1
00:01:03,953 --> 00:01:08,686
1805年4月  拿破仑在欧洲所向无敌

2
00:01:08,758 --> 00:01:12,125
只有英国舰队能阻止他

3
00:01:12,194 --> 00:01:14,788
汪洋大海成为生死战场

4
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:59,788
怒海争锋: 极地远征

5
00:02:05,981 --> 00:02:08,108
"惊奇号"

6
00:02:08,184 --> 00:02:10,516
28管大炮  197名船员

7
00:02:10,586 --> 00:02:12,747
巴西北海岸

8
00:02:14,323 --> 00:02:17,349
海军部命令欧杰克舰长

9
00:02:17,426 --> 00:02:21,795
拦截法国私掠船 "地狱号"

10
00:02:21,864 --> 00:02:25,163
它想要航向太平洋掀起大战

11
00:02:25,234 --> 00:02:27,862
击沉  烧毁或抢夺它

12
00:04:14,856 --> 00:04:18,883
没事了
Come on. It's all right.

13
00:04:18,993 --> 00:04:21,188
没事了
Yes, it's all right.

14
00:04:29,037 --> 00:04:31,232
威尔  醒醒
Wake up, Will.

15
00:04:37,712 --> 00:04:40,306
右舷有动静
Starboard bow ahoy.

16
00:04:48,656 --> 00:04:51,181
-什么东西?  斯莱德  -我好像听到声音
-What is it, Slade? -Thought I heard somethin'.

17
00:04:51,259 --> 00:04:53,352
好像是铃声
Sounded like a bell.

18
00:04:54,929 --> 00:04:59,161
-也许是渔船  -或是警示浮筒
-Native fishermen, perhaps. -Or a reef marker, sir.

19
00:04:59,234 --> 00:05:02,203
科勒米  测量水深
Mr Calamy, the lead, if you please.

20
00:05:17,118 --> 00:05:21,282
-水深五英寻  -五英寻
-By the mark, five fathom. -Five fathom.

21
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:38,769
只有沙子和贝壳
Sand and broken shell.

22
00:05:45,613 --> 00:05:47,911
怎么了?
What is it?

23
00:05:49,984 --> 00:05:52,612
右舷22度半浓雾中有东西
Two points off the starboard bow, in the fog bank.

24
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,745
什么东西?  船帆吗?
What was it? A sail?

25
00:05:54,822 --> 00:05:59,316
-我不知道  -该击鼓备战吗?
-I don't know what it was. -Should we beat to quarters?

26
00:06:06,601 --> 00:06:10,970
-我不确定  -你可是值星官
-I can't be certain. -You're officer of the watch.

27
00:06:11,072 --> 00:06:14,064
哈伦  你要做决定
Hollom, you must make a decision.

28
00:06:15,610 --> 00:06:17,908
击鼓备战
We shall beat to quarters.

29
00:06:20,114 --> 00:06:23,277
起来  快起来
Rouse up. Sleepers awake.

30
00:06:27,522 --> 00:06:29,615
动作快点
Move. Move along.

31
00:06:29,691 --> 00:06:32,819
快点  快呀
Jump to it, boys. Jump to it.

32
00:06:34,295 --> 00:06:36,195
向那边  快去
Light along there.

33
00:06:57,986 --> 00:06:59,613
浓雾中有动静
Sighting in heavy fog.

34
00:06:59,687 --> 00:07:03,214
-爬上船桅  -把小艇放下去
-Handsomely on the yards tackle. -Topmen aloft.

35
00:07:12,033 --> 00:07:14,297
在哪里?
Where away?

36
00:07:14,369 --> 00:07:19,136
右舷22度半不到一英里
Two points off the starboard bow, sir. Not a mile distant.

37
00:07:22,043 --> 00:07:25,012
-你确定吗?  -确定
-You sure, Mr Hollom? -Yes, sir.

38
00:07:26,381 --> 00:07:28,474
是军舰吗?
Man-of-war?

39
00:07:30,485 --> 00:07:32,350
我不知道
I don't know, sir.

40
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:36,254
它一闪而过  我只看到影子
It was only for a moment. I thought I saw a shape.

41
00:07:39,193 --> 00:07:42,492
-你有看到吗?  科勒米  -没有
-Did you see it, Mr Calamy? -No, sir.

42
00:07:44,565 --> 00:07:49,229
你做得对  回到岗位去
You did the right thing, Mr Hollom. Go to your stations.

43
00:07:50,705 --> 00:07:53,071
汤姆  你来指挥
The deck's yours, Tom.

44
00:07:53,174 --> 00:07:54,607
是
Sir.

45
00:07:57,111 --> 00:08:00,911
把小艇放下去  用力拉紧
Clear away. And launch boats.

46
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:11,720
-把它搬下去回到岗位  -你们听到了
-Quit your dawdling. -You heard the man.

47
00:08:11,793 --> 00:08:14,261
放下去
Lower away.

48
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,224
大家用力拉
Haul both your yard tackles.

49
00:08:23,538 --> 00:08:25,301
敲钟
Strike the bell.

50
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:54,900
趴下  快趴下
Down. All hands down.

51
00:09:09,317 --> 00:09:13,413
全体备战  霍拉  损坏报告
Hands to your stations. Mr Hollar, damage report, if you please.

52
00:09:22,530 --> 00:09:26,364
18磅重炮弹造成  我要逼近它用右舷大炮迎敌
18-pounders. We'll have to get closer. Run out the starboard battery.

53
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:30,267
艾伦  迎风转向  逼近敌舰旁边
Mr Allen, come up on the wind. Lay me alongside at pistol-shot.

54
00:09:36,444 --> 00:09:38,674
狙击手爬到制高点  霍华德
Sharpshooters to the tops, Mr Howard.

55
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:41,340
带你的手下爬上主桅
Sergeant. Take your section into the main top.

56
00:09:41,449 --> 00:09:44,384
抬头挺胸英勇抗敌
We stand tall on the quarterdeck. All of us.

57
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:48,489
-波义耳  升旗  -是  船长
-Mr Boyle, run up the colors. -Aye, sir.

58
00:09:53,494 --> 00:09:57,453
记在船长日志上  "第六声钟响时迎敌"
Note for the log, Mr Watt. "Engaged enemy frigate at six bells."

59
00:09:57,519 --> 00:09:59,180
誓死奋战

60
00:10:01,969 --> 00:10:04,563
-笔直地冲过去  -冲过去
-Straight at 'em, Mr Mowett. -Straight at 'em, sir.

61
00:10:04,672 --> 00:10:07,072
比尔
Bill.

62
00:10:07,175 --> 00:10:10,042
别拿剑  下去
Leave the swords. Get the captain's silver below.

63
00:10:10,144 --> 00:10:14,171
还没进入射程  等到接近了再开炮
She's not in range yet. Stand fast till she's close enough.

64
00:10:14,248 --> 00:10:18,082
-再靠近一点  -遵命
-Close with him amidships. -Midships it is, sir.

65
00:10:18,753 --> 00:10:21,085
千万别弄掉了
For God's sake, don't drop anything.

66
00:10:26,394 --> 00:10:27,588
稳住
Steady.

67
00:10:27,695 --> 00:10:31,222
-坚守岗位  -坚守岗位  勇敢一点
-Hold your positions. -Hold your position. Courage, now.

68
00:10:32,366 --> 00:10:36,700
-稳住了稳住了  -我们会让他们好看
-Hold steady, boys. -Don't worry, lads, we'll serve 'em out yet.

69
00:10:36,771 --> 00:10:41,174
你受伤了长官  戴维斯  杰米  把他带下去
Mr Pullings, sir. Davies, Jemmy, get Mr Pullings below.

70
00:10:41,242 --> 00:10:42,903
是  长官
Aye, sir.

71
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:45,535
布雷克尼  通知船长
Mr Blakeney, pass the word for the captain.

72
00:10:45,613 --> 00:10:48,377
赶快清理
Clear the forward pin rails.

73
00:10:54,789 --> 00:10:56,416
沙子多洒一点
More sand on the floor.

74
00:10:58,025 --> 00:11:00,084
乘着浪头  开炮
On the up-roll, fire!

75
00:11:13,107 --> 00:11:14,768
趴下
Down!

76
00:11:23,751 --> 00:11:28,279
保护舵柄  来人  把伤者抬下去
Relieving-tackles on the tiller. You men, collect these wounded.

77
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:35,486
-继续开炮  -重新装弹药
-Keep 'em spitting, Mr Calamy. -Aye, sir. Reload and give 'em hell.

78
00:11:59,341 --> 00:12:01,571
"地狱号"

79
00:12:01,656 --> 00:12:03,954
船长  快到船尾
Sir. To the taffrail.

80
00:12:10,498 --> 00:12:13,592
方向舵损坏  无法掌舵
The rudder's shot away. The steering don't answer.

81
00:12:13,668 --> 00:12:15,966
我们成了瓮中之鳖
We're fish in a barrel.

82
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:25,542
怎么不开炮?
Why are we not firing?

83
00:12:30,017 --> 00:12:31,507
让我过去
Let me through.

84
00:12:31,619 --> 00:12:34,110
这儿  乔
Here, Joe.

85
00:12:34,188 --> 00:12:36,281
快塞住
Hold it in there.

86
00:12:40,728 --> 00:12:45,722
-他在左船首  -拿出手枪
-He's on the larboard bow, sir. -Bring up your small arms.

87
00:12:48,836 --> 00:12:51,327
准备抗敌登船
Prepare to repel boarders.

88
00:12:51,405 --> 00:12:54,568
拿了枪  等船长下令
Seize your weapons and wait for the word.

89
00:12:56,677 --> 00:12:59,009
请下令
Your orders, sir?

90
00:12:59,981 --> 00:13:04,350
叫炮兵到甲板船尾绑绳索  下去划小艇
Call the gun crews to deck. Rig man-ropes over the stern and pull the boats in.

91
00:13:04,418 --> 00:13:07,012
把船拖进浓雾
Put us in that fog, Tom.

92
00:13:17,999 --> 00:13:20,524
用力划拼命划  大家一起划
Pull together, men.

93
00:13:20,601 --> 00:13:22,728
划进浓雾
Pull for the fog bank.

94
00:13:24,105 --> 00:13:26,665
大炮搬过来
Run 'em out.

95
00:13:31,045 --> 00:13:32,706
开炮
Fire!

96
00:13:34,015 --> 00:13:38,042
船身破裂  快塞住缺口
She's opened up a seam. We need to get some oakum and pound it in.

97
00:13:38,119 --> 00:13:40,883
拿槌子和铁条
Joe, a mallet and some irons.

98
00:13:46,794 --> 00:13:49,024
它追上来了
She's gaining on us.

99
00:13:56,137 --> 00:14:00,073
-我们快要摆脱了  -快划呀
-We're nearly there, boys. -Pull.

100
00:14:00,141 --> 00:14:03,372
-用力划呀  -进了那团雾就好了
-Reach for it, men. -We're home inside that fog.

101
00:14:08,115 --> 00:14:09,446
开炮
Fire!

102
00:14:11,052 --> 00:14:13,953
为杰克船长用力划
Pull for Lucky Jack.

103
00:14:14,055 --> 00:14:16,216
成功了
We've done it.

104
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:21,392
不要出声
Pipe down. Silence on deck.

105
00:14:31,305 --> 00:14:34,433
他们不会找到我们
They'll not find us in here.

106
00:14:34,508 --> 00:14:38,137
安静  不准大喊大叫
Quiet, lads. No shouts, no calls.

107
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:08,335
不要划了
Avast rowing.

108
00:15:11,278 --> 00:15:13,678
干得好  各位
Well done, lads.

109
00:15:37,705 --> 00:15:41,038
水只淹到两英尺六英寸  就停了
Two feet six inches, sir, and holding.

110
00:15:44,678 --> 00:15:47,408
-干得好  拉姆  -谢谢
-Good work, Mr Lamb. -Thank you, sir.

111
00:15:57,992 --> 00:16:00,153
有多少人伤亡?
So, what's the butcher's bill?

112
00:16:00,227 --> 00:16:02,821
9人阵亡  27人受伤
Nine dead, 27 wounded.

113
00:16:12,072 --> 00:16:13,539
乔・普雷斯
Joe Plaice.

114
00:16:13,607 --> 00:16:16,452
他的头骨破裂  很严重
He has a severely depressed fracture of the skull. 

115
00:16:16,453 --> 00:16:18,943
恐怕撑不过今晚
I don't think he'll see out the night.

116
00:16:19,046 --> 00:16:21,844
布雷克尼勋爵
Lord Blakeney.

117
00:16:24,218 --> 00:16:26,516
我只是断了只手臂
Just a broken arm, sir.

118
00:16:27,788 --> 00:16:30,757
你不用担心
You're in very good hands.

119
00:16:35,462 --> 00:16:39,057
你跟他父亲是好朋友  我会尽力而为
I'm doing everything I can. I know you were close to his father.

120
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:43,536
他父亲一定会谅解  他的母亲就...
His father would've understood. He knew the life. His mother, however...

121
00:16:43,604 --> 00:16:47,096
我看看你的伤口
Let me take a look at that brow of yours.

122
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,073
什么?
What?

123
00:16:53,814 --> 00:16:56,908
他很厉害  突然冒出来进行偷袭
Damn, he was good. Just came out of nowhere.

124
00:16:56,984 --> 00:17:02,115
先开炮来个下马威  然后攻击船尾把方向舵打断
Hit us with a full broadside, cut across our tail and took out our rudder.

125
00:17:02,223 --> 00:17:04,453
对方的炮兵神准
Damn fine gunnery.

126
00:17:05,426 --> 00:17:10,090
起浓雾我们才能脱身  运气真好
We only slipped away because of the fog. Quite fortunate, really.

127
00:17:10,164 --> 00:17:14,931
他有上风优势  我有老天保佑
He may have had the weather gauge, but we had the weather gods.

128
00:17:15,970 --> 00:17:19,471
我不太明白你在说什么  
I have no idea what it is you're talking about, 

129
00:17:19,472 --> 00:17:21,806
不过他是蛮厉害的
but he did seem to come off rather well.

130
00:17:22,743 --> 00:17:28,079
我们航行了七个礼拜  他却知道在哪里偷袭我们
Seven weeks sailing, and he happens in darkness on our exact position.

131
00:17:30,417 --> 00:17:34,581
法军在英国和各地都有间谍  我们也一样
The French have their spies in England and elsewhere. As do we.

132
00:17:35,189 --> 00:17:37,089
没错
Indeed.

133
00:17:38,292 --> 00:17:44,356
他若知道我们在找他  就该闪避
If he knew we were looking for him, he could have stood to sea and passed well clear.

134
00:17:44,465 --> 00:17:47,628
也许他也在找我们
Well then, perhaps he was looking for us.

135
00:18:04,439 --> 00:18:06,498
暗礁

136
00:18:09,344 --> 00:18:11,778
暗沙

137
00:18:13,827 --> 00:18:16,352
它不是护卫舰才有鬼
If she was a frigate, then I am a Dutchman.

138
00:18:16,463 --> 00:18:19,398
敌强我弱  输了并不丢脸
It was an unfair match. There was no dishonor in it.

139
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,730
它是艘二重甲板船
She was more like a ship of the line.

140
00:18:21,835 --> 00:18:25,168
你会不禁对它的船身感到惊讶
You have to wonder about her hull. Our shots wouldn't penetrate.

141
00:18:25,239 --> 00:18:27,867
从两百码外开炮都伤不了它
Triple-shotted at 200 yards -no effect.

142
00:18:27,975 --> 00:18:31,706
它有上风优势和猛烈的炮火优势
She had the weather gauge and a clear advantage in firepower.

143
00:18:31,812 --> 00:18:34,372
什么是上风优势?
What is the weather gauge?

144
00:18:34,481 --> 00:18:38,008
-你要我画给你看吗?  -别在桌布上乱画
-Shall I show you again, Stephen? -Not on the cloth.

145
00:18:40,087 --> 00:18:44,217
它的位置在上风处  所以能左右战局
It means she had the wind in her favor, therefore control of the engagement.

146
00:18:44,325 --> 00:18:47,658
它的大炮也射得比我们远
And she had longer guns, so she could hit us beyond our range.

147
00:18:47,728 --> 00:18:51,391
承认吧  我们一败涂地
The simple fact is we were soundly beaten.

148
00:18:53,834 --> 00:18:58,931
-拿破仑在太平洋部署重型护卫舰  -这样一来他就稳操胜算
-Heavy frigate like that in the Pacific... -Could tip the war in Napoleon's favor.

149
00:18:59,506 --> 00:19:04,569
跟这艘军舰比起来  "惊奇号" 太老了
By comparison, the Surprise is a somewhat aged man-of-war.

150
00:19:08,282 --> 00:19:13,083
-我说错了吗?  -你说我老了吗?
-Am I not correct? -Would you call me an aged man of war?

151
00:19:13,187 --> 00:19:16,520
"惊奇号" 并不老  一点都不老
The Surprise is not old. No one would call her old.

152
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:22,756
它的船首方正船身线条优美  船坚炮利  迅速敏捷
She has a bluff bow, lovely lines. She's a fine sea boat, weatherly, stiff and fast.

153
00:19:22,863 --> 00:19:26,230
看是谁操纵了  可以非常快
Very fast, if she's well-handled.

154
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:28,427
它一点都不老
No, she's not old.

155
00:19:29,737 --> 00:19:31,762
它正值黄金年华
She's in her prime.

156
00:19:31,872 --> 00:19:36,434
主桅和后帆需要修复  前桅帆破裂  要用备用帆
We can patch up the main and mizzen. Foresail's gone, so we'll bend our spare.

157
00:19:36,543 --> 00:19:40,604
拉姆认为只要稍作修补  我们就能安全返航
Mr Lamb is confident with basic repairs. We can get home as we are.

158
00:19:40,714 --> 00:19:43,547
我们还不回去
We're not going home.

159
00:19:52,459 --> 00:19:56,623
修船一定要靠岸  "地狱号" 可能还在找我们
But to refit we need a port, and the Acheron may be still looking for us.

160
00:19:56,730 --> 00:20:01,064
我们可以在海上修船  这儿有暗沙的浅水海域
We can refit at sea. Here, where it shoals.

161
00:20:02,269 --> 00:20:07,002
地狱号要到南太平洋开战  我们必须阻止它
As you said, she is taking the war to the South Seas. We are supposed to stop her.

162
00:20:07,107 --> 00:20:14,343
但是请恕我直言  它的实力比我们强太多了
But, sir...with respect...she's a vastly heavier ship. She's out of our class.

163
00:20:15,282 --> 00:20:18,979
等我们修好船它都到合恩角了
She could be halfway to Cape Horn by the time we're repaired.

164
00:20:19,086 --> 00:20:22,783
那就更不能浪费时间
Well then, there's not a moment to lose.

165
00:20:41,175 --> 00:20:44,338
最后一针是穿过鼻孔吗?
Is it true they put the last stitch through your nose?

166
00:20:44,445 --> 00:20:46,504
什么意思?
What do you mean?

167
00:20:47,548 --> 00:20:49,513
乔说  你死后  
Joe said when you die, 

168
00:20:49,514 --> 00:20:52,884
他们会在你鼻孔上面缝一针
they stitch you in your hammock with the last stitch in your nose,

169
00:20:52,986 --> 00:20:56,183
确定你不是在睡觉
just to make sure you're not asleep.

170
00:20:59,827 --> 00:21:03,285
别缝我的鼻孔好不好?
Not through the nose. You'll tell them?

171
00:21:59,953 --> 00:22:04,447
没关系鸦片酊能止痛
It's all right. It's just the laudanum speaking.

172
00:22:38,058 --> 00:22:40,822
你是最勇敢的病人
I've never seen a braver patient.

173
00:22:45,666 --> 00:22:49,727
放心  我很快会把你修好
Poor darling. Never mind, soon have you fixed up.

174
00:22:49,803 --> 00:22:51,771
快去工作
I want good work now.

175
00:22:51,838 --> 00:22:56,332
两个人去修补前桅板  罗伯茨  查德威克
I'll need two men into the starboard forechannels. Roberts, Chadwick.

176
00:22:56,443 --> 00:22:58,502
做得很好
That's nice work there.

177
00:22:58,612 --> 00:23:01,911
这修不好的  这些给我更换掉
Repair won't do here. I need these replaced.

178
00:23:08,622 --> 00:23:11,955
科勒米  你一定有兴趣
Mr Calamy. There's something might interest you here.

179
00:23:12,025 --> 00:23:16,621
你看  这是船长当见习官时刻的
Look. The captain carved that. When he was a mid, no more than your age.

180
00:23:16,697 --> 00:23:18,597
他从小就待在这艘船上
He's known this ship man and boy.

181
00:23:18,665 --> 00:23:21,883
这艘船上流了太多他的血  
He says there's enough of his blood in the woodwork 

182
00:23:21,884 --> 00:23:23,864
几乎算是他的亲人
for the ship to almost be a relation.

183
00:23:23,971 --> 00:23:28,203
我同意你的说法  你真是知识渊博
I do understand your point. Your knowledge is beyond question.

184
00:23:28,308 --> 00:23:32,210
但是如果现在才去找木材  
However, a week in the Brazilian rain forest 

185
00:23:32,211 --> 00:23:33,712
一定来不及
looking for a new mast simply will not do.

186
00:23:33,814 --> 00:23:36,044
"地狱号" 早就到中国了
The Acheron will be halfway to China.

187
00:23:36,149 --> 00:23:41,883
拉姆会尽全力抢修船身  大家都要跟他一样
Mr Lamb, as always, will do his best. Which is all I can hope to expect from any man.

188
00:24:15,922 --> 00:24:17,719
那是他的脑浆吗?
Is them his brains?

189
00:24:17,824 --> 00:24:21,692
不这是血浆  这才是他的大脑
No, that's just dried blood. Those are his brains.

190
00:24:27,034 --> 00:24:30,367
他可是妙手回春的医生
Physician, he is. Ain't one of your common surgeons.

191
00:24:30,437 --> 00:24:33,600
把硬币给我
-Can I have the coin, please? -Sir.

192
00:24:38,345 --> 00:24:41,075
他在陆地上不轻易替人看病
He wouldn't look at you for under ten guineas on land.

193
00:24:41,181 --> 00:24:43,342
他也很了解鸟兽习性
And he knows his birds and beasts.

194
00:24:43,417 --> 00:24:46,784
他连甲虫在想什么都知道
You show him a beetle and he'll tell you what it's thinking.

195
00:24:46,887 --> 00:24:50,414
回去做事吧懒虫  吹哨子
Back to work, you loafers. Eckhart, use your pipe.

196
00:24:50,524 --> 00:24:52,924
赶快回去做事
Let's get on with it, gentlemen.

197
00:24:53,026 --> 00:24:56,792
别净在这儿打混
You're not a pennyweight of use gawpin' here.

198
00:25:03,403 --> 00:25:05,963
他还是没开口
Still hasn't said a word, sir.

199
00:25:11,411 --> 00:25:14,403
布雷克尼勋爵  好点吗?
Lord Blakeney. Feeling better?

200
00:25:14,481 --> 00:25:16,574
好多了  谢谢
Much better, thank you, sir.

201
00:25:16,650 --> 00:25:18,743
那就好
Well, good. Good.

202
00:25:20,620 --> 00:25:24,750
医生说你很爱看书  所以我...
The doctor told me you were fond of reading, so I...

203
00:25:26,948 --> 00:25:30,907
《纳尔逊将军的胜仗》

204
00:25:30,997 --> 00:25:34,489
有他打的胜仗和很棒的插图
It has all of his major battles and some fine illustrations.

205
00:25:34,601 --> 00:25:36,501
谢谢你  船长
Thank you, sir.

206
00:25:37,738 --> 00:25:40,298
你见过纳尔逊将军吗?
Did you ever meet Lord Nelson, sir?

207
00:25:40,407 --> 00:25:44,104
我为他打过尼罗河战役  伟大的胜仗
I had the honor of serving with him. At the Nile. A great victory.

208
00:25:44,177 --> 00:25:50,275
这本书上有记载  如果我没记错是第135页
You can find it in here, actually. Page 135, if I'm not mistaken.

209
00:25:51,685 --> 00:25:53,585
是的
Yes.

210
00:25:59,493 --> 00:26:03,361
他是个什么样的人?
May I beg you to tell me what kind of man he is?

211
00:26:05,599 --> 00:26:07,590
你只要看书就知道
You should read the book.

212
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:10,261
我会的  谢谢
I will, sir. Thank you.

213
00:26:30,957 --> 00:26:36,054
他们又在拉了  叽叽嘎嘎
Here we go again. Scrape-scrape, screech-screech.

214
00:26:36,163 --> 00:26:40,065
没有一首能跳舞  喝得烂醉了也不行
Never a tune you could dance to, not if you were drunk as Davy's sow.

215
00:26:49,976 --> 00:26:51,807
这样如何?
How about this?

216
00:26:51,878 --> 00:26:56,338
你想来首激昂的曲子吗?
Or are you in the mood for something more aggressive?

217
00:28:05,006 --> 00:28:07,531
"挚爱的苏菲..."

218
00:28:09,723 --> 00:28:11,884
敬礼
Salute.

219
00:28:11,958 --> 00:28:13,892
脱帽
Hats off.

220
00:28:16,062 --> 00:28:18,223
什么事?
What's all this about?

221
00:28:20,967 --> 00:28:24,300
-这是什么?  -那艘鬼船
-What's this? -It's the phantom, sir.

222
00:28:24,404 --> 00:28:28,170
大家都说 "地狱号" 是鬼船
Excuse me. That's what the men call it. It's the Acheron, sir.

223
00:28:28,275 --> 00:28:31,176
他看到它的建造过程
You see, Will here, he seen her being built.

224
00:28:31,278 --> 00:28:36,443
在波士顿  在战前  它是美国佬建造的
In Boston, sir. During the peace. But she's Yankee-built, sir.

225
00:28:36,516 --> 00:28:40,452
他在那里结婚  他妻子的表弟在船坞工作
He was getting married, and his wife's second cousin works in the yards,

226
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:42,784
带他看过那艘船
so Will here saw the ship out of water.

227
00:28:42,856 --> 00:28:48,123
我看到那艘船有点古怪  所以就请乔...
Sir, I saw there was something right strange about her, so I asked Joe...

228
00:28:48,194 --> 00:28:51,493
我照他说的做了模型
So he described it to me and I knocked you up a model, sir.

229
00:28:51,598 --> 00:28:56,331
-这个模型很准确?  -完全准确
-And this framing is accurate? -Exactly accurate, sir.

230
00:28:56,436 --> 00:28:58,996
-谢谢两位  -谢谢
-Thank you, lads. -Thank you, sir.

231
00:28:59,105 --> 00:29:02,336
多给他们一份朗姆酒
Killick, an extra ration of rum for these men.

232
00:29:02,442 --> 00:29:04,842
谢谢船长
Thank you very much, sir.

233
00:29:04,945 --> 00:29:07,937
-那是留着过节喝的  -过节喝葡萄酒
-Which I was saving for Salutin' Day. -We'll drink wine.

234
00:29:08,014 --> 00:29:10,141
不可思议
Oh, drink wine on Salutin' Day.

235
00:29:10,216 --> 00:29:12,878
上宽下窄的船首
Bluff above the water and sharp below.

236
00:29:12,986 --> 00:29:18,390
流线形的船身  所以船速才会那么快
Gives the hull a finer entry and a long run as she goes aft. That's why she's so fast.

237
00:29:18,491 --> 00:29:21,119
船身虽重  船速却很快
Heavier, but fast despite it.

238
00:29:22,162 --> 00:29:27,498
这是未来的设计  我们生活的时代真是无比惊奇
That's the future. What a fascinating modern age we live in.

239
00:29:27,567 --> 00:29:31,469
它的船壳至少有两英尺厚
Planking and framing like that would make her hull 2ft thick. Solid oak.

240
00:29:31,538 --> 00:29:36,498
怪不得射不穿  船速最快大概能到12至14节
That's why we couldn't dent her. She's probably capable of making 12 to 14 knots.

241
00:29:37,177 --> 00:29:40,510
多亏有瓦利跟他妻子的表弟
Now we know. Thank God for Warley and his wife's second cousin.

242
00:29:40,580 --> 00:29:43,549
它一天能航行280英里
She could be doing up to 280 miles a day.

243
00:29:43,650 --> 00:29:49,680
就算追得上它  想要击败它...
Even if we did catch up with her, I mean, to take her...

244
00:29:49,756 --> 00:29:53,886
比登天还难  它有44管大炮
She's out of our class. She's a 44-gun ship.

245
00:29:55,495 --> 00:29:59,932
它的罩门跟我们一样是船尾
She's still vulnerable at the stern, like the rest of us.

246
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,706
亲爱的  一个吻多少钱?
Hello, darling. How much for a kiss?

247
00:30:17,450 --> 00:30:19,509
(葡萄牙语) 一个吻多少钱?
Quanto cost-o kiss-o?

248
00:30:19,586 --> 00:30:22,783
-你的名字?  -我叫玛莉亚
-Name? -My name is Maria.

249
00:30:22,889 --> 00:30:26,188
我要用斧头换箭  快点
Give us arrows. I give ax. Quick, mate.

250
00:30:26,259 --> 00:30:28,523
谢谢
Thank you, mate.

251
00:30:37,137 --> 00:30:40,072
借过一下
Gangway for the mail, please.

252
00:30:41,207 --> 00:30:44,608
拿去  这是重要的邮件
Here we are. Very important mail. Letters.

253
00:30:44,711 --> 00:30:47,976
他说什么?
What's he saying?

254
00:30:51,584 --> 00:30:55,418
一艘法国战舰  10号在这里靠岸后往南航行
A large man-of-war, French, stopped here on the 10th, then headed south.

255
00:31:01,161 --> 00:31:02,992
附近的某处
Somewhere here.

256
00:31:03,096 --> 00:31:05,656
比我们快三星期
A full three weeks ahead.

257
00:31:05,765 --> 00:31:07,630
可恶
Damn.

258
00:31:08,568 --> 00:31:11,332
汤姆  赶快完成交易
All right, Tom, let's get all this squared away.

259
00:31:11,438 --> 00:31:15,340
霍拉  尽快完成交易
Aye, sir. Mr Hollar. Let us complete our business here.

260
00:31:15,442 --> 00:31:18,172
准备起锚
Hands, prepare to weigh anchor.

261
00:31:20,146 --> 00:31:22,246
别光顾着泡妞  
Put that woman down, Slade. 

262
00:31:22,247 --> 00:31:27,348
这是皇家海军  不是让你来逛窑子的
This is a ship of His Majesty's Navy, not a floating bordello.

263
00:31:30,156 --> 00:31:34,286
大家动手  把补给品搬上去
All hands, get these provisions stowed.

264
00:31:46,773 --> 00:31:48,365
很好
Well done.

265
00:31:48,475 --> 00:31:50,534
各位
Gentlemen.

266
00:31:51,544 --> 00:31:56,538
敬妻子和情人
To wives and to sweethearts.

267
00:31:56,649 --> 00:32:00,016
愿她们永不相见
May they never meet.

268
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:04,022
霍华德  把酒瓶拿来
Mr Howard, the bottle. The bottle stands by you, sir.

269
00:32:04,624 --> 00:32:06,956
船长?
Sir?

270
00:32:07,794 --> 00:32:12,356
布雷克尼说  你为纳尔逊将军打过仗
Excuse me, sir, but Mr Blakeney said that you served under Lord Nelson at the Nile.

271
00:32:12,465 --> 00:32:17,368
没错  当年我是个年轻的上尉  年纪跟你差不多
Indeed. I was a young lieutenant, not much older than you are now.

272
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:21,031
普灵只是个见习官
And Mr Pullings was a sniveling midshipman,

273
00:32:21,141 --> 00:32:23,507
还一直吵着想回家
still yearning for hearth and home.

274
00:32:23,576 --> 00:32:26,739
你见过他吗?  能谈谈他吗?
Did you meet him, sir? Can you tell me what he's like?

275
00:32:26,846 --> 00:32:29,974
我很荣幸与他共餐两次
I have had the honor of dining with him twice.

276
00:32:30,049 --> 00:32:32,916
他两次都有跟我说话
He spoke to me on both occasions.

277
00:32:33,019 --> 00:32:36,182
他是个有远见的战略家
A master tactician and a man of singular vision.

278
00:32:36,256 --> 00:32:41,523
他打仗时总是说  "别用什么战略  冲上去就打"
He always said in battle "Never mind the maneuvers, just go straight at 'em."

279
00:32:41,594 --> 00:32:45,758
他也许没谋略  却有领导才能
Some would say not a great seaman, but a great leader.

280
00:32:45,865 --> 00:32:48,891
英国要靠他对抗拿破仑
He's England's only hope if old Boney intends to invade.

281
00:32:49,002 --> 00:32:52,369
请你说说他的趣事
Sir, might we press you for an anecdote?

282
00:32:55,341 --> 00:32:58,401
他第一次跟我说的话
The first time that he spoke to me,

283
00:32:58,511 --> 00:33:03,710
我永远也忘不了  好像是昨天一样
I shall never forget his words. I remember it like it was yesterday.

284
00:33:03,783 --> 00:33:07,549
他从餐桌另一边看着我说:
He leaned across the table, he looked me straight in the eye,

285
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:12,284
"奥布里  请把盐瓶递给我"
and he said "Aubrey, may I trouble you for the salt?"

286
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:19,525
我一直试着模仿他的口气
I've always tried to say it exactly as he did ever since.

287
00:33:25,305 --> 00:33:30,709
第二次他说了个故事
The second time, the second time he told me a story

288
00:33:30,777 --> 00:33:34,304
有人在寒夜里请他穿大衣
about how someone offered him a boat cloak on a cold night.

289
00:33:34,414 --> 00:33:39,283
他并没有穿  他说他很暖和
And he said no, he didn't need it. That he was quite warm.

290
00:33:39,385 --> 00:33:44,049
他的爱国心让他全身暖呼呼
His zeal for king and country kept him warm.

291
00:33:44,123 --> 00:33:48,150
听起来很做作  如果是别人
I know it sounds absurd, and were it from another man,

292
00:33:48,261 --> 00:33:53,563
我一定瞧不起他  觉得他很假
you'd cry out "What pitiful stuff" and dismiss it as mere enthusiasm.

293
00:33:53,633 --> 00:33:55,726
但出自纳尔逊的口
But with Nelson,

294
00:33:57,604 --> 00:34:00,437
你知道那是真心话
you felt your heart glow.

295
00:34:06,779 --> 00:34:11,739
-对吧普灵  -没错
-Wouldn't you say, Mr Pullings? -You did indeed, sir.

296
00:34:12,318 --> 00:34:18,780
他是唯一没被权力腐化的人
Well then, he would seem to be the exception to the rule that authority corrupts.

297
00:34:18,858 --> 00:34:22,191
敬纳尔逊将军
To Lord Nelson.

298
00:34:25,965 --> 00:34:29,332
你看到这两只小虫吗?
Do you see those two weevils, Doctor?

299
00:34:29,435 --> 00:34:30,959
看到了
I do.

300
00:34:31,037 --> 00:34:33,369
你会选哪一只?
Which would you choose?

301
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:40,310
这两只其实一模一样  它们都是象鼻虫
Neither. There's no difference between them. They're the same species of curculio.

302
00:34:40,380 --> 00:34:42,814
如果你非选不可呢?
If you had to choose.

303
00:34:42,882 --> 00:34:46,340
必须要做出一个抉择的话...
If you were forced to make a choice. If there was no other...

304
00:34:46,452 --> 00:34:50,047
如果你硬要我选
Well then, if you're going to push me,

305
00:34:52,358 --> 00:34:55,350
我会选右边这只
I would choose the right-hand weevil.

306
00:34:55,461 --> 00:34:59,192
它看起来比较凶恶
It has significant advantage in both length and breadth.

307
00:34:59,299 --> 00:35:02,632
我赢了  你被我说倒了
There, I have you. You're completely dished.

308
00:35:02,702 --> 00:35:08,641
你要知道  在军中有句话说  二恶相权取其轻
Do you not know that in the service one must always choose the lesser of two weevils?

309
00:35:15,315 --> 00:35:18,716
这笑话太冷了
He who would pun would pick a pocket.

310
00:35:20,219 --> 00:35:22,483
逊毙了
Really. Weevils.

311
00:35:22,555 --> 00:35:27,891
二恶相权取其轻
To the lesser of two weevils.

312
00:35:38,538 --> 00:35:41,507
乔
Yay, Joe.

313
00:35:44,043 --> 00:35:46,102
乔  继续
Go on, Joe.

314
00:36:04,764 --> 00:36:07,062
上帝可以收回我的灵魂
The Lord taketh,

315
00:36:08,267 --> 00:36:11,202
也可以把它还给我
and the Lord giveth away.

316
00:36:11,270 --> 00:36:14,137
听到吗?  他开口了耶
You hear that? He said something.

317
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:17,107
医生  他说话了
Doctor. He spoke, Doctor.

318
00:36:17,210 --> 00:36:19,110
干得好  史蒂芬
Well done indeed, Stephen.

319
00:36:19,212 --> 00:36:22,204
*Adieu to you Spanish ladies*

320
00:36:22,281 --> 00:36:26,411
*Farewell and adieu to you ladies of Spain*

321
00:36:26,486 --> 00:36:31,423
*For we've received orders to sail for old England*

322
00:36:31,491 --> 00:36:37,657
*We hope in a short time to see you again*

323
00:36:38,564 --> 00:36:42,728
哈伦的歌声真好听
What a wonderfully true voice Mr Hollom possesses.

324
00:36:42,802 --> 00:36:45,327
是啊
Indeed.

325
00:36:46,472 --> 00:36:49,168
*Come, all you bold young thoughtless men*

326
00:36:49,275 --> 00:36:51,766
*A warning take by me*

327
00:36:51,844 --> 00:36:56,440
*And never leave your happy homes to sail the raging sea*

328
00:37:08,194 --> 00:37:11,322
海上有动静
On deck there. Sail ho.

329
00:37:12,298 --> 00:37:14,493
好像是一艘船
Looks like a frigate.

330
00:37:19,105 --> 00:37:21,198
它怎么来的?
How did it get there?

331
00:37:21,307 --> 00:37:24,970
-我们一定要转过去迎敌  -但是它又有上风优势
-We must turn and fight. -But he has the weather gauge again.

332
00:37:25,044 --> 00:37:28,343
它一定早就在等我们上钩
He must've been watching us from some inlet.

333
00:37:32,318 --> 00:37:35,845
它吃定我们了  怎么办?
My God. What can we do? He has us by the hip.

334
00:37:35,955 --> 00:37:37,946
逃得越快越好
Run like smoke and oakum.

335
00:37:38,024 --> 00:37:41,960
-船帆不够用  -若有必要连手帕都要用上
-We'll have to bend every sail. -We'll put up our handkerchiefs if we have to.

336
00:37:42,028 --> 00:37:45,987
我们一定要逃走  快去吧  艾伦
We must survive this day. Let's get about it. Mr Allen, gentlemen.

337
00:37:46,065 --> 00:37:48,124
全体船员  扬帆
All hands, make sail.

338
00:37:48,201 --> 00:37:53,138
这是他第二次占上风  不会有第三次
This is the second time he's done this to me. There will not be a third.

339
00:38:09,021 --> 00:38:14,755
那是一艘恶魔开的鬼船
I tell ya, the devil's at the wheel of that there phantom ship.

340
00:38:14,861 --> 00:38:17,261
你最好小心点
You better hold fast.

341
00:38:23,536 --> 00:38:25,697
这家伙跟我有仇吗?
What is it with this man?

342
00:38:25,771 --> 00:38:31,573
我是不是杀了他的亲人?  他的爱子?
Did I kill a relative of his in battle, perhaps? His boy, God forbid?

343
00:38:31,677 --> 00:38:33,702
他的作风跟你很像  杰克
He fights like you, Jack.

344
00:38:52,298 --> 00:38:55,233
把太阳调到海平线上
Bring the sun down to the horizon.

345
00:38:55,301 --> 00:38:59,533
当它碰到海平线  威廉森  注意看
When its lower limb is touching the horizon... Williamson, look to your sextant.

346
00:38:59,605 --> 00:39:03,473
当太阳不再动
When the orb is no longer rising,

347
00:39:03,576 --> 00:39:07,137
它就达到了顶点  那就是正午
then it has reached its zenith and that would be noon.

348
00:39:07,246 --> 00:39:09,612
-船长  -普灵
-Sir? -Mr Pullings.

349
00:39:09,715 --> 00:39:11,910
-你会了吗?  -会了
-Do you make noon, Mr Hollom? -Yes, sir.

350
00:39:11,984 --> 00:39:14,475
那就去教他们吧
Call noon. It's your class.

351
00:39:16,789 --> 00:39:20,156
-正午了  -尼克斯  中午十二时
-Sir, that's noon. -Mr Nichols, make that twelve.

352
00:39:20,259 --> 00:39:22,591
还有六小时?
Six hours?

353
00:39:22,662 --> 00:39:24,926
最多五小时
Five at most.

354
00:39:24,997 --> 00:39:28,956
天黑前别被它追上来
Just keep us out of her reach until nightfall.

355
00:39:37,109 --> 00:39:42,012
它会跟我们一样  动作要快一点
She's to look like us, lads, don't forget. Jibbo, make fast those whips.

356
00:39:42,114 --> 00:39:45,572
风势太大  主桅不能做太高
We didn't want to make it any taller, on account of this wind.

357
00:39:45,651 --> 00:39:51,783
-他们在做什么?  -你的第一艘船
-Excuse me, sir, but what are they building? -Your first command.

358
00:39:57,663 --> 00:40:00,029
快点  它要追上来了
Quickly. She'll be on top of us.

359
00:40:00,132 --> 00:40:03,033
放下吊在船桅上的木筏
Take the weight on the yard tackles.

360
00:40:03,135 --> 00:40:05,433
把木筏推出去
Fend her off.

361
00:40:05,504 --> 00:40:07,995
放下去
Lower away on the main.

362
00:40:14,981 --> 00:40:18,144
-我可不想失去你  -是  先生
-Wouldn't want to lose you. -Aye, sir.

363
00:40:29,228 --> 00:40:34,791
那里有系索  把它拖到船尾
There's a painter. Pass her aft. Outside everything, mind.

364
00:40:34,867 --> 00:40:39,167
快  它十分钟后就能追上来
Lively now. We've not ten minutes before he's up with us.

365
00:40:45,344 --> 00:40:49,178
-记着船长教你的  -用力拉
-Mind what the captain told you. -Pull, boys. That's it.

366
00:41:12,738 --> 00:41:13,762
现在
Now.

367
00:41:19,445 --> 00:41:22,380
基里克  熄灯
Killick there. Douse your light.

368
00:41:28,788 --> 00:41:30,415
艾伦  准备好
Mr Allen, make ready.

369
00:42:11,564 --> 00:42:14,055
我们钓到一条大鱼
Hello. We caught a fish.

370
00:42:15,601 --> 00:42:17,501
你来掌舵  波登
Take the helm, Bonden.

371
00:42:17,603 --> 00:42:21,300
这很好玩吧
-Now, tell me that wasn't fun. -Yes, sir.

372
00:42:23,075 --> 00:42:25,771
左满舵
Hard a'larboard.

373
00:42:54,673 --> 00:42:59,167
叫大家下去休息  我来值星
Stand the men down, Mr Pullings. I'll take this watch.

374
00:42:59,278 --> 00:43:00,870
是  长官
Aye, sir.

375
00:43:00,980 --> 00:43:05,542
莫维  艾伦  别出声  快去吧
Mr Mowett, Mr Allen, calmly now. You know his orders.

376
00:43:05,651 --> 00:43:07,710
干得好
Well done, sir.

377
00:43:09,522 --> 00:43:14,118
它一定是艘鬼船  它突然就跟在后面
She's a right phantom, she is. The way she come up again, right behind us like that.

378
00:43:14,193 --> 00:43:19,529
不晓得从哪儿冒出来  就像第一次在浓雾中出现
Out of nowhere. And right behind us. Like that first time, out the fog.

379
00:43:19,632 --> 00:43:22,123
用大炮打它都没用
With our shot bouncin' off her.

380
00:43:22,201 --> 00:43:25,170
难怪船长的绰号是幸运杰克
Captain's not called Lucky Jack for no reason.

381
00:43:25,237 --> 00:43:29,333
不管怎样它还是艘私掠船  幸运杰克会打败它的
Phantom or no, she's a privateer, and Lucky Jack'll have her.

382
00:43:29,408 --> 00:43:32,343
对付鬼船不能只靠运气
You need more than luck 'gainst a phantom.

383
00:43:34,146 --> 00:43:37,377
-那是海盗船吗?  -他们不是海盗
-Is she like a pirate? -No, they're not pirates, Lofty.

384
00:43:37,483 --> 00:43:42,011
如果是的话  我们就能把他们吊死
Oh, no. If they were, we could hang them when we catch 'em.

385
00:43:42,087 --> 00:43:44,885
法国佬给私掠船的命令是
Privateer gets a piece of paper from the Frenchies

386
00:43:44,990 --> 00:43:47,652
只要看到英国船就可以开炮
says they can hunt down anything with our flag.

387
00:43:47,726 --> 00:43:51,389
他们也抢了不少商船
They go after rich merchantmen and the like.

388
00:43:51,497 --> 00:43:55,228
逮到他们就能分不少钱
But think on our share of the prize money.

389
00:43:55,334 --> 00:44:00,328
船上一定有很多黄金  龙涎香  还有用不完的金银珠宝
She'll be loaded with gold and ambergris and all the gems of Araby.

390
00:44:00,406 --> 00:44:03,898
就算发了财也得活着回家
That's all very well, Nagle. Got to get home to spend it, but.

391
00:44:04,009 --> 00:44:06,341
死人可不会请我喝酒
Never met a dead man who bought me a drink.

392
00:44:06,412 --> 00:44:10,371
你也没请活人喝过酒
And I've never met a live one that you bought one for, neither.

393
00:44:11,750 --> 00:44:17,882
你何必三更半夜挨寒受冻  最后一杯咖啡
Sitting up all night, catching your death of cold. That's the last of the coffee, too.

394
00:44:17,957 --> 00:44:20,050
谢谢你
Thank you, Killick.

395
00:44:24,396 --> 00:44:26,421
波登
Bonden.

396
00:44:26,532 --> 00:44:29,695
不必向东了  设定航向  西南偏南
That's enough easting. Set a course sou'-sou'west.

397
00:44:29,768 --> 00:44:33,761
遵命  西南偏南
Aye, sir. Sou'-sou'west.

398
00:44:37,810 --> 00:44:40,278
前有船只
Sail.

399
00:44:40,379 --> 00:44:43,576
右舷船首22度半
Two points off starboard bow.

400
00:44:44,116 --> 00:44:46,584
幸运杰克万岁
Three cheers for Lucky Jack.

401
00:44:52,725 --> 00:44:55,091
是我们的了
She's ours, boys.

402
00:45:04,837 --> 00:45:09,001
你赢了
Foul. You got away before me.

403
00:45:13,178 --> 00:45:16,147
升起高低前桅帆
-Set royals and courses. -Sir.

404
00:45:16,248 --> 00:45:18,739
叫人站在栏杆边
Have the idlers placed along the rails.

405
00:45:18,817 --> 00:45:20,785
他太神了
I've never seen the like.

406
00:45:20,853 --> 00:45:24,812
绕一百海里后咬住敌舰船尾
It has to be more than 100 sea miles and he brings us up on his tail.

407
00:45:24,924 --> 00:45:29,088
这才叫航海高手
That's seamanship, Mr Pullings. My God, that's seamanship.

408
00:45:29,161 --> 00:45:32,494
我就说会成功  天黑就能追上去
Told you it would work, Will. We'll have them by nightfall.

409
00:45:32,598 --> 00:45:36,090
-他们死定了  -风向对我们有利
-I think we've got him, sir. -And the wind favors us this time.

410
00:45:36,168 --> 00:45:39,467
话别说的太早
Don't count your eggs before they're in the pudding.

411
00:45:39,538 --> 00:45:44,475
不过只要能追上去  就能逮到他们
Still, if we can close this gap and get up behind her, she may well be ours.

412
00:45:44,543 --> 00:45:46,943
老天保佑快刮强风
Touch wood. Scratch a stay.

413
00:45:47,546 --> 00:45:51,141
转三圈  愿老天保佑我们
Turn three times. May the Lord and saints preserve us.

414
00:46:06,632 --> 00:46:08,327
转过来
Turn.

415
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:12,234
动作快点  快把救生索绑好
Move along, man. We'll have lost him before you rig it up.

416
00:46:12,338 --> 00:46:14,465
停
Hold.

417
00:46:15,240 --> 00:46:18,835
-船速十二节  -十二节  很好
-12 knots, sir. -That's 12 knots. That's good.

418
00:46:18,911 --> 00:46:23,575
再多点  派人站到上风面
I want more. Have all the spare hands placed on the windward rail.

419
00:46:23,682 --> 00:46:26,981
霍拉  把大家都叫起来
Mr Hollar. Rouse up the off-watch.

420
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:31,253
全都站到右舷栏杆
All hands on starboard rail.

421
00:46:31,924 --> 00:46:35,325
迎风扬起左顶帆
Come up the larboard topsail sheets.

422
00:46:52,945 --> 00:46:57,405
-船帆全都升起  -超过极限  船帆就会被吹走
-We're crackin' on. -We'll be crackin' up if he don't watch it.

423
00:46:57,516 --> 00:47:02,112
船长知道这艘船的极限
Captain knows this ship. He knows what she can take.

424
00:47:06,291 --> 00:47:10,728
把前后救生索绑好
Mr Hollar, I want lifelines fore and aft.

425
00:47:10,796 --> 00:47:12,525
别偷懒
No lounging, boy.

426
00:47:12,598 --> 00:47:18,298
前后救生索把小艇绑牢
Lifelines, fore and aft. Double-grape that launch.

427
00:47:20,539 --> 00:47:22,939
那是合恩角
Cape Horn, Doctor.

428
00:47:38,757 --> 00:47:41,749
快盖起来  这儿的水够多了
Close the lid. There's enough water in the grog.

429
00:47:41,827 --> 00:47:43,727
多谢了
Thank you for that, Davies.

430
00:47:43,796 --> 00:47:48,665
船长还想追下去吗?
Reckon the captain will follow him round the Horn, every stitch of canvas flying?

431
00:47:48,767 --> 00:47:51,235
就算追到地狱  他也要追上去
I reckon he'd follow him to the gates of hell.

432
00:47:51,303 --> 00:47:55,831
那艘恶魔船要把我们带入陷阱
It's a devil ship, I tell ya. And it's leadin' us right into a trap.

433
00:47:59,244 --> 00:48:02,111
它要带我们冲向合恩角
She's making a run for the Horn, sir.

434
00:48:02,181 --> 00:48:05,150
我很怕船桅会被吹断
I'll not vouch for this mast. Not around the Horn.

435
00:48:05,250 --> 00:48:08,276
我会把你的话记在日志
Thank you. Your comments will be noted in the log.

436
00:48:08,353 --> 00:48:14,622
掌帆员站好岗位  风太大了  快收帆
Sail trimmers to their stations. Get the sails off her, lads. She's over-pressed.

437
00:48:14,693 --> 00:48:16,854
用力拉下来
Give 'em a pull and belay.

438
00:48:32,344 --> 00:48:35,836
就快追到了  我不会放弃
We're closing on her, Tom. I'll not give up now.

439
00:48:35,948 --> 00:48:39,179
迎风转向  设定航向  西南偏西
Come up on the wind, Barret. Set a course sou'west by west.

440
00:48:39,284 --> 00:48:41,878
遵命  西南偏西
Sou'west by west, sir.

441
00:48:43,055 --> 00:48:44,784
科勒米
Mr Calamy.

442
00:48:44,857 --> 00:48:47,553
西南偏西
Idlers and waisters below.

443
00:48:51,363 --> 00:48:54,161
我们要去合恩角
We're for the Horn, boys.

444
00:48:58,137 --> 00:49:00,071
把顶帆收起来
Close reef topsails.

445
00:49:13,585 --> 00:49:15,348
快点  伙计们
Lively, lads.

446
00:49:19,658 --> 00:49:24,425
封舱  别等沉船了就来不及了
Batten down those hatches before we're on the bottom.

447
00:49:34,006 --> 00:49:36,839
约翰逊  图拉维  收起后帆
Johansson, Truelove. To the mizzen.

448
00:49:38,243 --> 00:49:40,177
都绑紧了
All secure.

449
00:49:40,245 --> 00:49:42,213
很好
Down ye go, lads.

450
00:49:48,687 --> 00:49:53,386
帮瓦利把后桅顶帆拉下来
Mr Hollom, help young Warley on the mizzen topgallant.

451
00:49:56,862 --> 00:50:00,229
-我需要更多人手  -快去
-I'll need more men, sir. -Yes. Go.

452
00:50:08,574 --> 00:50:12,271
哈伦  帮帮我
Mr Hollom, sir. Help me.

453
00:50:19,084 --> 00:50:22,747
快去帮忙
Tudor, Ellers. To Mr Allen.

454
00:50:22,821 --> 00:50:27,815
爬上去把后桅顶帆收起来
You men, lay aloft. The mizzen topgallant. Light along.

455
00:50:35,767 --> 00:50:37,826
救命啊
Help.

456
00:50:40,906 --> 00:50:42,931
救命啊
Help me.

457
00:50:48,814 --> 00:50:51,578
有人落海
Man overboard.

458
00:50:52,751 --> 00:50:57,245
后桅没有了  大伙到船艉
Mizzen's gone. Hands to the taffrail.

459
00:51:08,333 --> 00:51:11,200
在那儿
He's over there, sir.

460
00:51:11,303 --> 00:51:14,966
快游过去  快点
Swim for the wreckage, man. Swim.

461
00:51:15,774 --> 00:51:17,469
我在这儿
Over here.

462
00:51:17,542 --> 00:51:22,844
快把木桶等等能浮的东西都丢下海
Mr Allen, gratings and barrels, anything that floats, overboard.

463
00:51:22,948 --> 00:51:27,044
船身在倾斜  就快翻船了
She's broaching. We're losing her.

464
00:51:27,152 --> 00:51:30,485
残骸会把船身拖下去
Sir, the wreckage is acting as a sea anchor.

465
00:51:30,555 --> 00:51:34,116
不砍断救生索就会沉船
We must cut it loose. It's going to sink us.

466
00:51:34,192 --> 00:51:38,026
他就快游到了
Sir, he's going to make it. He can do it.

467
00:51:38,130 --> 00:51:42,157
-加油  -快游呀
-Come on, Will. -Come on. Hand over hand.

468
00:51:42,234 --> 00:51:47,399
快游呀  快游过去  就快沉船了
For God's sake, Will, swim. Swim for the wreckage, Will.

469
00:51:56,048 --> 00:51:57,982
你行的
You can do it, Will.

470
00:51:58,050 --> 00:52:02,214
-加油  -加油  威尔
-Swim. Come on. -Come on, Will. Swim.

471
00:54:04,630 --> 00:54:08,066
1805年直布罗陀  瓦利

472
00:54:08,134 --> 00:54:10,432
重返家园

473
00:54:31,870 --> 00:54:35,306
-他又来了  -谁?
-He's been at it again. -Who's that, then?

474
00:54:35,373 --> 00:54:38,206
-瘟神  -什么东西?
-The Jonah. -What's that?

475
00:54:48,587 --> 00:54:53,047
打仗时  战死比较能令人接受
The deaths in actual battle are the easiest to bear.

476
00:54:53,758 --> 00:55:00,823
死在我的手术刀下  或是因为感染而死的弟兄
For my own part, those who die under my knife, or from some subsequent infection,

477
00:55:00,899 --> 00:55:06,838
我总是说他们是死在敌人手上  不是死在我手上
I have to remind myself that it was the enemy that killed them, not me.

478
00:55:09,007 --> 00:55:11,601
他是战争的牺牲者
That young man was a casualty of war.

479
00:55:14,346 --> 00:55:18,578
你也说二恶相权取其轻
As you said yourself, you have to choose the lesser of two evils.

480
00:55:18,683 --> 00:55:20,742
小虫
Weevils.

481
00:55:24,189 --> 00:55:28,592
瓦利人缘很好  船员都会很难过
The crew will take it badly. Warley was popular.

482
00:55:28,693 --> 00:55:32,754
他们有向你反映什么吗?
Have they expressed any feelings on the matter to you?

483
00:55:40,038 --> 00:55:43,064
我在回答之前要先问下
Jack, before answering, I'm compelled to ask,

484
00:55:43,141 --> 00:55:47,271
我该把你当朋友还是船长?
am I speaking with my old friend or to the ship's captain?

485
00:55:48,380 --> 00:55:51,975
我会跟船长说我最痛恨内奸
To the captain I'd say there's little I detest more than an informer.

486
00:55:52,083 --> 00:55:55,314
-你活像个爱尔兰人  -我就是爱尔兰人
-Now you're talking like an Irishman. -I am an Irishman.

487
00:55:55,420 --> 00:55:57,445
那就把我当朋友
As a friend, then.

488
00:55:57,556 --> 00:56:03,392
身为你的朋友  我从没怀疑过你当船长的能力
As a friend, I would say that I have never once doubted your abilities as a captain.

489
00:56:03,461 --> 00:56:05,395
有话就直说吧
Speak plainly, Stephen.

490
00:56:07,165 --> 00:56:11,898
也许我们早就该返航
Perhaps we should have turned back weeks ago.

491
00:56:11,970 --> 00:56:15,838
跟随幸运杰克的弟兄们
The men, of course they would follow Lucky Jack anywhere,

492
00:56:15,941 --> 00:56:18,171
都很有自信能打胜仗
rightfully confident of victory.

493
00:56:18,276 --> 00:56:23,908
这就是问题所在  你很少吃败仗
But therein lies the problem. You're not accustomed to defeat.

494
00:56:25,450 --> 00:56:29,066
追逐这艘比我们更强的战舰  
And chasing this larger, faster ship with its long guns 

495
00:56:29,067 --> 00:56:31,650
也许是你的自尊心在作祟
is beginning to smack of pride.

496
00:56:31,756 --> 00:56:35,157
这不是自尊  这是我的职责
It's not a question of pride. It is a question of duty.

497
00:56:35,260 --> 00:56:37,694
职责  你说的好伟大哦
Duty. Yes, I've heard it well spoken of.

498
00:56:37,796 --> 00:56:42,426
尽管嘲笑我吧  反正你只会在鸡蛋里挑骨头
Be as satiric as you like. Viewing the world through a microscope is your prerogative.

499
00:56:42,500 --> 00:56:43,940
这是艘战舰  
This is a ship of war. 

500
00:56:43,941 --> 00:56:47,028
为了尽好职责  我什么都愿意做
I will grind whatever grist the mill requires to fulfill my duty.

501
00:56:47,138 --> 00:56:49,504
甚至不惜一切?
Whatever the cost?

502
00:56:49,608 --> 00:56:51,838
不惜一切
Whatever the cost.

503
00:56:51,943 --> 00:56:54,707
盲目地服从命令
To follow orders with no regard for cost.

504
00:56:54,813 --> 00:56:59,113
这难道不是意气用事吗?
Can you really claim there's nothing personal in this call to duty?

505
00:56:59,184 --> 00:57:01,675
军人的天职就是服从命令
