Then his entire gun crew's killed. Soon as he went up the mizzen, Will falls.

665
01:14:15,419 --> 01:14:19,219
换他值星  结果风就停了?
And whose watch was it when we lost our wind?

666
01:14:41,578 --> 01:14:44,206
你站住
You there. Stand fast.

667
01:14:46,350 --> 01:14:50,514
把他带下去  铐起来
Master-at-arms, take that man below and clap him in irons.

668
01:14:50,587 --> 01:14:54,114
第八钟响时举行鞭刑
Mr Pullings, defaulters at eight bells.

669
01:14:54,224 --> 01:14:55,919
遵命
Aye, sir.

670
01:14:57,361 --> 01:15:00,694
把哈伦带到我的舱房
Bring Hollom down to my cabin.

671
01:15:04,702 --> 01:15:07,967
你被他顶撞了怎么一句话也不说?
A man pushed past you, yet you said nothing. Why?

672
01:15:08,072 --> 01:15:10,973
我想说  却说不出口
I intended to, sir, but the right words didn't...

673
01:15:11,075 --> 01:15:16,274
说不出口?  他这是以下犯上
The right words? He was deliberately insubordinate.

674
01:15:16,380 --> 01:15:19,440
我试着跟他们做朋友
I've tried to get to know the men, sir, and be friendly,

675
01:15:19,550 --> 01:15:22,986
他们却故意整我
but they've taken a set against me.

676
01:15:23,654 --> 01:15:28,489
老在我背后说我坏话  不停地给我白眼
Always whispering when I go past and giving me looks.

677
01:15:28,592 --> 01:15:31,493
以后我会对他们凶一点
I'll set that to rights. I'll be much tougher on them.

678
01:15:31,595 --> 01:15:35,122
你不能跟水手做朋友
You don't make friends with the foremastjacks, lad.

679
01:15:35,232 --> 01:15:39,498
他们会看不起你
They'll despise you in the end, think you weak.

680
01:15:39,603 --> 01:15:43,300
你也不必当暴君
-Nor do you need to be a tyrant. -No, sir.

681
01:15:43,407 --> 01:15:45,671
是  对不起
I'm very sorry, sir.

682
01:15:45,776 --> 01:15:49,177
-你26还是27岁?  -下礼拜就满30了
-You're 26? 27? -I'm 30 next Friday, sir.

683
01:15:49,279 --> 01:15:50,837
30
30?

684
01:15:50,948 --> 01:15:54,179
你两次考上尉都没过
You've failed to pass for lieutenant twice.

685
01:15:54,284 --> 01:15:59,153
你表现不差  也有航海知识  你不能一辈子都当见习官
I know you have, but you're not a bad sailor. You can't spend your life a midshipman.

686
01:15:59,256 --> 01:16:02,851
是的  我会更努力
No, sir. I will try much harder, sir.

687
01:16:04,428 --> 01:16:07,829
听好  他们需要的是领导
Look, Hollom, it's leadership they want.

688
01:16:07,931 --> 01:16:09,956
还有力量
Strength.

689
01:16:10,033 --> 01:16:15,494
找出自身那种特质  就会得到他们的尊敬
You find that within yourself, and you will earn their respect.

690
01:16:17,107 --> 01:16:20,668
没有尊敬哪来的纪律?
Without respect, true discipline goes by the board.

691
01:16:21,779 --> 01:16:24,543
是的
Yes, sir.

692
01:16:24,648 --> 01:16:29,711
力量  尊敬  还有纪律
Strength, respect and discipline, sir.

693
01:16:33,657 --> 01:16:37,616
这是件很遗憾的事
It's an unfortunate business, Hollom.

694
01:16:38,629 --> 01:16:41,462
实在遗憾
Damned unfortunate.

695
01:16:42,199 --> 01:16:45,066
-下去吧  -是
-That'll be all. -Yes, sir.

696
01:16:48,338 --> 01:16:52,331
-我也不喜欢鞭刑  -大家都认为是哈伦...
-I am not a flogging captain. -Hollom is a scapegoat for all the bad luck,

697
01:16:52,409 --> 01:16:55,708
带来霉运
real or imagined, on this voyage.

698
01:16:55,813 --> 01:16:58,338
请你过来
Mr Lamb? If you please.

699
01:16:58,415 --> 01:17:01,680
他们都筋疲力尽
They're exhausted. These men are exhausted.

700
01:17:01,752 --> 01:17:04,653
你把他们操练得太凶
You've pushed them too hard.

701
01:17:04,721 --> 01:17:08,384
我是请你来跟我聊天
Stephen, I invite you to this cabin as my friend.

702
01:17:08,492 --> 01:17:12,758
不是质疑我的命令
Not to criticize nor to comment on my command.

703
01:17:12,863 --> 01:17:18,392
我是不是该等你气消了才来?
Shall I leave you until you're in a more harmonious frame of mind?

704
01:17:19,670 --> 01:17:23,436
-你要我怎样?  -把船上的酒都倒掉
-What would you have me do? -Tip the ship's grog over the side.

705
01:17:23,540 --> 01:17:26,998
-不给他们喝酒?  -纳格当时喝醉了
-Stop their grog? -Nagle was drunk when he insulted Hollom.

706
01:17:27,077 --> 01:17:30,376
你要我取消两百年的传统
Stop 200 years of privilege and tradition.

707
01:17:30,447 --> 01:17:33,610
他们有酒喝就不会叛变
I'd rather have them three sheets to the wind than face a mutiny.

708
01:17:33,717 --> 01:17:36,015
我倒能理解他们会想叛变
I'm rather understanding of mutinies.

709
01:17:36,086 --> 01:17:40,921
他们离乡背井  被困在监狱一般的船上...
Men pressed from their homes, confined for months aboard a wooden prison...

710
01:17:41,024 --> 01:17:47,793
我很尊重你的意见  但是我不能承受船员叛变
I respect your right to disagree with me, but I can only afford one rebel on this ship

711
01:17:49,233 --> 01:17:53,533
你看不起海军就是看不起我
I hate it when you talk of the service in this way. It makes me so very low.

712
01:17:53,604 --> 01:17:55,367
你以为我想鞭打纳格吗?
You think I want to flog Nagle?

713
01:17:55,439 --> 01:17:59,034
他跟我切断绳子  害他好友送死
A man who hacked the ropes that sent his mate to his death?

714
01:17:59,109 --> 01:18:01,976
在我的命令下
Under my orders?

715
01:18:02,079 --> 01:18:06,413
看到没  没有纪律  这艘船就会一团混乱
Do you not see? The only things that keep this wooden world together are hard work...

716
01:18:06,483 --> 01:18:08,917
他只是没向长官敬礼
Jack, the man failed to salute.

717
01:18:08,986 --> 01:18:11,716
连大自然都有阶级之分
There's hierarchies even in nature.

718
01:18:11,788 --> 01:18:17,055
-大自然没有鄙视和羞辱  -不管他们是不行的
-There is no disdain in nature. There is no... -Men must be governed.

719
01:18:17,127 --> 01:18:19,652
有时候管不好 但一定要管
Often not wisely, but governed nonetheless.

720
01:18:19,763 --> 01:18:24,063
这是史上每个暴君的藉口 从尼禄到拿破仑都一样
That's the excuse of every tyrant in history, from Nero to Bonaparte.

721
01:18:24,134 --> 01:18:28,264
我反对独裁专制 那只会带来痛苦与迫害
I, for one, am opposed to authority. It is an egg of misery and oppression.

722
01:18:28,338 --> 01:18:32,798
你想搞革命来错地方了
You've come to the wrong shop for anarchy, brother.

723
01:18:35,646 --> 01:18:37,477
四
Four.

724
01:18:38,949 --> 01:18:40,314
五
Five.

725
01:18:42,619 --> 01:18:44,280
六
Six.

726
01:18:45,522 --> 01:18:47,319
七
Seven.

727
01:18:48,592 --> 01:18:50,116
八
Eight.

728
01:18:50,827 --> 01:18:52,590
九
Nine.

729
01:18:54,965 --> 01:18:56,830
十
Ten.

730
01:18:57,935 --> 01:18:59,129
十一
Eleven.

731
01:19:01,171 --> 01:19:03,139
十二
Twelve.

732
01:19:06,143 --> 01:19:08,338
把他放下来
Cut him down.

733
01:19:32,302 --> 01:19:34,668
轻声一点
Not so loud.

734
01:20:28,792 --> 01:20:31,454
把刀子放下来
Put that dirk down, Boyle.

735
01:20:33,964 --> 01:20:36,558
你没事吧?
You OK, Mr Hollom?

736
01:20:36,633 --> 01:20:39,727
-他没病  只是想偷懒  跟以前一样  -闭嘴
-He's not ill, just dodging work as usual. -Shut up.

737
01:20:39,803 --> 01:20:42,897
-你闭嘴  -别管他
-You shut up. -Just leave him be.

738
01:20:42,973 --> 01:20:45,965
-喝一点水  -谢谢你
-Have some water. -Thank you.

739
01:20:50,213 --> 01:20:52,545
哈伦生病了
Sir, it's Mr Hollom.

740
01:20:59,656 --> 01:21:05,617
他的身体没病  他认为自己受到诅咒
There's nothing physically wrong with him. He thinks he's been cursed.

741
01:21:07,397 --> 01:21:11,094
水手什么都不怕  只怕碰到瘟神
Sailors can abide a great deal, but not a Jonah.

742
01:21:11,768 --> 01:21:14,828
你怎么也信怪力乱神这一套
My God. You believe it too.

743
01:21:16,506 --> 01:21:19,964
不是每件事都有科学根据的
Not everything is in your books, Stephen.

744
01:21:26,483 --> 01:21:28,417
就是他对吧?
It's him, innit?

745
01:21:30,987 --> 01:21:33,979
他是瘟神
The Jonah.

746
01:21:34,091 --> 01:21:36,082
都是他害的
He's causing it.

747
01:21:38,595 --> 01:21:41,826
鬼船是他召来的
He's callin' it up, don't you see?

748
01:21:41,932 --> 01:21:46,596
每次他值星  那艘船就会出现
Every time he's on watch, that ship appears.

749
01:21:50,040 --> 01:21:52,702
等着瞧吧
You wait and see.

750
01:21:52,809 --> 01:21:57,803
今晚他值星  鬼船一定会出现
Anytime tonight, that ghost ship's gonna turn up.

751
01:21:58,982 --> 01:22:03,783
它会把我们带到十八层地狱
And it's gonna take us all with it, straight down to the hot place.

752
01:22:24,474 --> 01:22:26,806
哈伦
Mr Hollom.

753
01:22:26,877 --> 01:22:29,573
你吓了我一大跳
You gave me such a start.

754
01:22:32,048 --> 01:22:34,209
你好点了吗?
Are you feeling better now?

755
01:22:34,317 --> 01:22:37,844
好多了  谢谢
Yes. Much better, thank you.

756
01:22:49,166 --> 01:22:53,535
船长说明天就会起风
The captain thinks we'll get our wind tomorrow.

757
01:22:53,603 --> 01:22:55,696
一定会的
I'm sure of it.

758
01:23:24,634 --> 01:23:28,195
你一直都对我很好
You've always been very kind to me.

759
01:23:35,278 --> 01:23:37,712
再见了  布雷克尼
Goodbye, Blakeney.

760
01:24:27,518 --> 01:24:29,611
约拿书

761
01:24:45,982 --> 01:24:50,783
事实是  不是所有人都能如愿以偿
The simple truth is, not all of us become the men we once hoped we might be.

762
01:24:50,854 --> 01:24:53,823
但我们都是上帝的子民
But we are all God's creatures.

763
01:24:56,559 --> 01:25:00,893
如果有人对哈伦有微词
If there are those among us who thought ill of Mr Hollom,

764
01:25:01,831 --> 01:25:04,527
说过他坏话
or spoke ill of him,

765
01:25:06,236 --> 01:25:09,865
或是瞧不起他这个人
or failed him in respect of fellowship,

766
01:25:11,141 --> 01:25:14,668
我们乞求上帝的原谅
then we ask for your forgiveness, Lord.

767
01:25:14,744 --> 01:25:16,905
还有他的原谅
And we ask for his.

768
01:25:32,696 --> 01:25:35,256
赞美上帝
God be praised. Mr Mowett?

769
01:26:00,623 --> 01:26:03,091
停在那儿
Avast there.

770
01:26:16,806 --> 01:26:19,934
-有只鸟跟着我们  -什么鸟?
-Doctor, have you seen the bird? -What sort of bird?

771
01:26:20,043 --> 01:26:26,972
有点像信天翁  要不然就是大个海鸥  它又来了
Some sort of albatross. Either that, or he's a prodigious great mew. There it goes.

772
01:26:33,323 --> 01:26:37,259
那儿  它是我的
There he is. My bird. Damn.

773
01:26:38,928 --> 01:26:40,896
它在兜圈子
It's circling, lads.

774
01:26:48,004 --> 01:26:49,062
医生
Doctor?

775
01:26:49,139 --> 01:26:51,471
天  医生
My God. Doctor.

776
01:26:52,909 --> 01:26:57,744
对不起  那只鸟冲下来  我没看到你
I'm so sorry, man. The bird dropped low. I didn't see you.

777
01:27:00,450 --> 01:27:03,681
-科勒米  快去叫希根  -我没事
-Calamy, get Higgins. -I'm fine, Jack.

778
01:27:17,200 --> 01:27:19,998
子弹把一块布打进去了
The bullet took in a piece of shirt with it.

779
01:27:20,103 --> 01:27:25,131
不取出来就会生脓溃烂
Unless it's removed, it's gonna suppurate and fester.

780
01:27:25,208 --> 01:27:27,176
你行吗?
Are you equal to the task?

781
01:27:27,277 --> 01:27:33,341
我先得看医生的书  研究一些图片
I'll need to read up on the doctor's books. Study some pictures he has.

782
01:27:33,450 --> 01:27:35,350
研究图片?
Study some pictures?

783
01:27:35,452 --> 01:27:38,512
先让我搞清状况
It's just to get my bearings, that's all.

784
01:27:38,621 --> 01:27:45,220
在陆地上比较容易  不会摇摇晃晃
It'd be a lot easier if I were on dry land. You wouldn't have the...

785
01:27:45,328 --> 01:27:47,819
我行的  等着瞧
I'll manage. You'll see.

786
01:28:12,255 --> 01:28:15,986
海平线上有船帆  往西
Sail on the horizon, sir. Running west.

787
01:28:16,526 --> 01:28:19,393
我们不确定  但应该就是它
We're not sure, but we think it's her, sir.

788
01:28:23,333 --> 01:28:25,324
要去...
Better get...

789
01:28:26,703 --> 01:28:28,762
再见了医生
Goodbye, sir.

790
01:28:47,056 --> 01:28:51,117
就是那艘法国船
No mistakin' it. She's the Frenchie.

791
01:28:58,701 --> 01:29:01,864
你要击鼓备战吗?
Shall we beat to quarters, sir?

792
01:29:40,276 --> 01:29:42,767
跟我说  这是不是为了我
Tell me this wasn't on my account.

793
01:29:42,845 --> 01:29:47,976
当然不是  我只想下来走走  伸伸腿
No, not at all. I just needed to stretch my legs.

794
01:29:49,686 --> 01:29:52,120
轻点
Gently there.

795
01:29:58,861 --> 01:30:02,661
快点  准备好
Briskly now. Secure this line.

796
01:30:02,765 --> 01:30:06,030
每20码都有陆战队员驻守
Royal Marines posted every 20 yards, sir.

797
01:30:17,113 --> 01:30:19,673
-准备好了吗?  -好了
-All set, Higgins? -Yes, sir.

798
01:30:19,782 --> 01:30:22,182
不
No.

799
01:30:22,785 --> 01:30:25,777
我要自己来
I do this with my own hand.

800
01:30:31,227 --> 01:30:34,321
没事的话我就出去等
If everything is under control, I'll just be outside.

801
01:30:34,397 --> 01:30:37,491
你的手很稳  我需要你
A spare pair of steady hands wouldn't go amiss.

802
01:30:37,567 --> 01:30:43,062
除非你见到血就会昏倒
That is, if, of course, you have the constitution for this kind of thing.

803
01:30:43,473 --> 01:30:51,380
亲爱的医生  我什么血腥的场面都见过了
My dear doctor, I have been amongst and around wounds all my life.

804
01:30:51,914 --> 01:30:54,075
那就好
Good, then.

805
01:30:54,183 --> 01:30:59,246
把手放在我肚子上  我会叫你用力按
Put your hand on my belly, pressing firmly when I give the word.

806
01:30:59,355 --> 01:31:02,813
希根  手术刀
Higgins, the catling, if you please.

807
01:31:10,266 --> 01:31:12,530
巴丁  镜子
Padeen, please.

808
01:31:25,782 --> 01:31:28,273
探测器
The sounder, Mr Higgins.

809
01:31:29,686 --> 01:31:31,745
擦血
Swab.

810
01:31:41,798 --> 01:31:43,891
好
All right.

811
01:31:46,803 --> 01:31:50,068
希根  你要帮我把肋骨撑开来
Mr Higgins, you'll have to raise the rib.

812
01:31:52,875 --> 01:31:57,107
用力握住牵引器
Take a good grip with the square retractor.

813
01:32:00,583 --> 01:32:02,778
插进去
Right in.

814
01:32:02,885 --> 01:32:04,819
往上扳
And lift up.

815
01:32:04,921 --> 01:32:06,388
往上
Lift up.

816
01:32:19,469 --> 01:32:22,063
帮我擦血  我看不到
Swab, Jack. I can't see.

817
01:32:26,442 --> 01:32:29,468
你还好吧?
Are you all right?

818
01:32:39,455 --> 01:32:41,514
夹到了
I got it.

819
01:32:53,169 --> 01:32:55,467
按用力一点
A tad more pressure.

820
01:33:06,315 --> 01:33:09,011
-全都在吗?  -对
-Is that all of it? -Aye, sir.

821
01:33:09,719 --> 01:33:11,949
能完全缝回去
She'll patch up nicely.

822
01:33:12,021 --> 01:33:13,955
谢天谢地
Thank God I got it.

823
01:33:59,735 --> 01:34:01,566
很好喝
That's good.

824
01:34:11,080 --> 01:34:14,914
-我跟巴丁替你采集样本?  -真的吗?
-Padeen and I have been collecting for you. -Have you really?

825
01:34:15,017 --> 01:34:18,612
我连甲虫栖息的植物也带回来了
The beetles each come with a specimen of the plant they were found on.

826
01:34:18,721 --> 01:34:21,189
那只逃走了
Padeen, that one's got away.

827
01:34:21,257 --> 01:34:25,523
你要是愿意看的话  我做了一些笔记
Sir, I've made a few notes, if you want to see them.

828
01:34:41,544 --> 01:34:45,571
布雷克尼  你有当自然学家的料
Mr Blakeney, it would appear that you have the makings of a naturalist.

829
01:34:45,648 --> 01:34:52,577
我可以跟你一样文武双全
Perhaps I could combine them to be a sort of fighting naturalist, like you, sir.

830
01:34:54,757 --> 01:34:58,090
战争和科学不太搭轧
They don't combine too well, I find.

831
01:34:58,160 --> 01:34:59,218
好
Right.

832
01:34:59,295 --> 01:35:01,661
你还不能起来吧?
Should you really be getting up, sir?

833
01:35:01,764 --> 01:35:05,222
-你也是医生吗?  -不是
-Mr Blakeney, are you also a doctor? -No, sir.

834
01:35:05,301 --> 01:35:08,737
没错  巴丁  扶我
No, you're not. Padeen, if you please.

835
01:35:15,177 --> 01:35:19,614
你知道船长打算待多久吗?
How long does the captain intend that we stay? Do you know?

836
01:35:21,484 --> 01:35:23,952
-一个礼拜吧  -一礼拜?
-Oh, a week perhaps. -A week?

837
01:35:24,020 --> 01:35:28,081
-我并不急  -不是该去马克萨斯吗?
-There's no great hurry. -Mustn't we make haste for the Marquesas?

838
01:35:28,157 --> 01:35:31,092
我都不确定那是不是 "地狱号"
I'm not even sure it was the Acheron we sighted.

839
01:35:31,160 --> 01:35:34,033
就算是它也早就走远了  
And if it was, she'll be well away by now. 

840
01:35:34,034 --> 01:35:36,188
要找到它是海底捞针
Like looking for an honest man in parliament.

841
01:35:36,299 --> 01:35:41,430
趁英法和谈之前回家吧
No, we shall head home. Before peace breaks out with France, God forbid.

842
01:35:45,041 --> 01:35:48,477
你这份恩情我恐怕无法报答
I fear you may have burdened me with a debt I can never repay.

843
01:35:48,544 --> 01:35:53,777
用我的名字替灌木命名  全身带刺难以消灭的那种
Tosh. Name a shrub after me. Something prickly and hard to eradicate.

844
01:35:53,849 --> 01:35:58,513
灌木?  才不要  我要用你的名字替大乌龟命名
A shrub? Nonsense. I'll name a great tortoise after you.

845
01:35:58,621 --> 01:36:01,385
欧氏海龟
Testudo aubreii.

846
01:36:43,065 --> 01:36:46,398
东西收一收  该走了
Come on, pack up your things. We should be going.

847
01:36:46,502 --> 01:36:49,699
-回营地吗?  -不  到小岛另一端
-Back to camp, sir? -No, to the other side of the island.

848
01:36:49,772 --> 01:36:54,232
-至少要走十英里路  -那就更一刻也不能耽搁
-But, sir, that must be at least ten miles. -Then there's not a moment to lose.

849
01:36:54,343 --> 01:36:57,335
我在那儿看到过不会飞的鸬鹚
That's where I saw my flightless cormorant.

850
01:36:57,413 --> 01:36:59,347
走吧
Come on.

851
01:37:10,259 --> 01:37:13,228
长七英寸
Seven inches in length.

852
01:37:14,230 --> 01:37:16,255
宽四英寸
Four inches wide.

853
01:37:16,365 --> 01:37:18,856
颈长十五英寸
15-inches-long neck.

854
01:37:19,935 --> 01:37:24,269
最宽处的宽度是六英寸
Width at the widest point, six inches.

855
01:37:30,312 --> 01:37:33,873
可以用手抓它们  不会咬人
Padeen, put the net down and use your hands. They won't bite.

856
01:37:33,949 --> 01:37:36,213
这只不错
Here's a good one.

857
01:37:37,953 --> 01:37:40,717
小心抓
Pick them up carefully.

858
01:37:41,323 --> 01:37:44,224
我们该回去了
Sir, I think we should be getting back.

859
01:37:44,293 --> 01:37:49,788
在这儿军纪一点也没有用  我一定要找到鸬鹚
Naval discipline doesn't operate out here, Mr Blakeney. I must find that cormorant.

860
01:37:49,899 --> 01:37:52,561
要是它真的不会飞
And should it indeed prove flightless,

861
01:37:52,635 --> 01:37:56,469
你可以跟我并列名为发现者
you can join me at the Royal Society dinner as co-discoverer.

862
01:39:36,906 --> 01:39:39,204
我们要快一点
Sir, we must hurry.

863
01:39:41,410 --> 01:39:47,110
你来背他  放下来  别管了
Padeen, you must carry him. Put those down. Leave them. Just put everything down.

864
01:39:50,619 --> 01:39:53,383
把笼子打开
Open the cages.

865
01:40:07,803 --> 01:40:12,706
-快上船  各就各位  -方向舵向右
-All hands, unmoor ship. -Mr Allen, I'll have her on a starboard tack.

866
01:40:12,775 --> 01:40:15,972
帮忙把乌龟放好
Let's have hands to stow these tortoises.

867
01:40:16,078 --> 01:40:20,139
波登  方向舵向右
Barret Bonden, put your helm hard to starboard.

868
01:40:22,218 --> 01:40:25,619
它往南航行了两个钟头
He has a head start of two hours on us and he's bearing south.

869
01:40:25,721 --> 01:40:29,418
目的地一定是查理王岛  它在找清水
That can only mean King Charles Island. He's looking for water.

870
01:40:29,491 --> 01:40:36,659
就算追得上去也无法偷袭它  除非我们能隐形
If we caught up with her, to take her, we'd have to be bloody invisible.

871
01:40:37,900 --> 01:40:40,835
帆往右舷拉
Brace the yards to starboard.

872
01:40:50,112 --> 01:40:53,240
史蒂芬  你发现那只鸟了吗?
So, Stephen, did you get to see your bird?

873
01:40:53,315 --> 01:40:57,308
没有  不过...其实有啦  只是没办法抓到
No. Well, yes, but I couldn't catch one.

874
01:40:58,020 --> 01:41:00,989
我最大的发现是那艘鬼船
My greatest discovery was your phantom.

875
01:41:01,090 --> 01:41:06,118
没错  很遗憾你得把样本丢掉
Indeed it was. I'm sorry you had to leave the majority of your collection behind.

876
01:41:06,195 --> 01:41:12,191
其实呢  我跟威尔有一样有趣的发现
In actual fact, Mr Blakeney and I did make one very interesting find.

877
01:41:12,301 --> 01:41:14,963
是吗?
Is that right?

878
01:41:15,037 --> 01:41:17,301
让我猜猜  这是一根树枝?
Let me guess. A stick?

879
01:41:24,446 --> 01:41:26,505
告诉他
Tell him about it, Mr Blakeney.

880
01:41:26,615 --> 01:41:29,982
-这是罕见的竹节虫  -竹节虫?
-It's a rare phasmid, sir. -A phasmid?

881
01:41:30,052 --> 01:41:36,548
它为了躲避掠食者  可以伪装成树枝
It's an insect that disguises itself as a stick in order to confuse its predators.

882
01:42:04,708 --> 01:42:07,108
"妖女号"

883
01:42:28,877 --> 01:42:31,107
这也算是一种伪装
A nautical phasmid, Doctor.

884
01:42:31,213 --> 01:42:36,207
对敌人来说这就是一艘捕鲸船
At least, to a hungry eye, if one has an appetite for whalers.

885
01:42:36,285 --> 01:42:40,619
我打算从现在开始  多了解自然生物
I intend to take a greater interest in the bounty of nature from now on.

886
01:42:40,723 --> 01:42:45,251
没想到研究自然生态也能有助于提高海上战略水平
I had no idea that a study of nature could advance the art of naval warfare.

887
01:42:45,361 --> 01:42:47,352
我懂了
I see.

888
01:42:47,429 --> 01:42:50,557
我要设下陷阱逮这个掠食者
Now to pull this predator in close and spring our trap.

889
01:42:50,632 --> 01:42:52,122
-杰克?  -在
-Jack? -Yes.

890
01:42:52,234 --> 01:42:55,067
你才是掠食者
You're the predator.

891
01:42:56,305 --> 01:43:01,402
在那儿看不到船身
There. Hull-down, broad off the larboard bow.

892
01:43:01,477 --> 01:43:03,411
就是它  没错
That's a frigate, all right.

893
01:43:03,479 --> 01:43:06,710
你的眼力真好
Damn, you've got good eyes, Barret.

894
01:43:06,782 --> 01:43:10,912
浓烟再多一点
-Mr Allen. More smoke. -Aye, sir.

895
01:43:10,986 --> 01:43:13,614
这样就能把它引过来
That'll bring 'em about.

896
01:43:24,466 --> 01:43:29,267
擦干净才会射得更直更准
That's it, lads. Clean 'em up so they fly straight and true.

897
01:43:31,807 --> 01:43:34,901
打火石要放进去
Let's have fresh flints in all the locks.

898
01:43:44,019 --> 01:43:48,854
把左舷大炮后轮卸下来
Larboard battery, unship your rear wheels.

899
01:43:53,362 --> 01:43:55,455
放下来
Drop the gun.

900
01:43:58,667 --> 01:44:02,296
-基里克  你也要换衣服  -天
-Come on, Killick, you too. Get dressed. -Oh, God.

901
01:44:02,371 --> 01:44:05,306
-汤姆  -一切准备就绪
-Tom? -Our preparations are completed, sir.

902
01:44:05,374 --> 01:44:10,107
很好  现在起  不准叫我长官  不准敬礼  不准鸣笛...
Good. Right, from now on no "sirs," no salutes, no whistles, no bells.

903
01:44:10,179 --> 01:44:11,840
是  长官
Aye, sir.

904
01:44:11,947 --> 01:44:15,542
...我们都不太习惯
Yes, I think we're all finding that quite difficult.

905
01:44:16,485 --> 01:44:19,477
地狱号上关了30名捕鲸船员
There'll be 30 or more whalers locked in the Acheron's hold.

906
01:44:19,555 --> 01:44:22,956
科勒米负责率人营救他们
After we board, Mr Calamy should take a party and free them.

907
01:44:23,025 --> 01:44:26,893
-他行吗?  -当年你行吗?
-You think him ready, sir? -Were you ready, Tom?

908
01:44:26,995 --> 01:44:29,793
-也许他能扭转战局  -没错
-He may well turn the tide. -Indeed, sir.

909
01:44:40,375 --> 01:44:42,639
它上钩了  转向
She's taken the bait. Let's come about.

910
01:44:42,711 --> 01:44:46,738
装成捕鲸船员  动作慌张
Make a show of fleeing, panicky and disorganized, like a whaler might.

911
01:44:46,849 --> 01:44:49,249
除了霍格以外
Present company excepted, Mr Hogg.

912
01:44:49,351 --> 01:44:51,216
各就各位  快点  别让他们看到
Hurry up, or they'll see you.

913
01:44:51,320 --> 01:44:55,552
别管了  快上来扮成捕鲸船员
Eckhart, leave that. Just come up quick and get some whaler's slops on.

914
01:45:08,737 --> 01:45:12,696
-恭喜了  彼得  你升了三副   -谢谢
-Congratulations. Acting third lieutenant. -Thank you.

915
01:45:12,774 --> 01:45:17,507
-听说我们要去营救捕鲸船员  -你要在后甲板留守
-I hear we're to free the whalers. -You're to be stationed on the quarterdeck.

916
01:45:17,579 --> 01:45:20,013
很遗憾
I'm sorry, Will.

917
01:45:21,950 --> 01:45:27,411
我要你们把船开得歪七扭八  让它迎风追上来
Make a bad show of keeping your course. Let her run up and luff every now and then.

918
01:45:28,223 --> 01:45:31,192
-对不起  -把帽子脱下来  我们是捕鲸人
-Excuse me, sir. -Remove your hat. We're whalers.

919
01:45:31,260 --> 01:45:35,458
我想跟你谈谈  科勒米说我不能登船进攻...
Mr Calamy says I'm not on the boarding party. I want to say...

920
01:45:35,564 --> 01:45:39,625
我知道你想说什么  我的答案是不行
I know what you want to say. And my answer is no.

921
01:45:39,735 --> 01:45:44,104
你要率领你的炮兵  等我登上敌舰后指挥这艘船
You'll lead your gun crew, then when we board, you'll take command of the ship.

922
01:45:44,206 --> 01:45:48,575
-你明白吗?  -你要我指挥这艘船?  谢谢
-Do I make myself clear? -Take command of the ship? Thank you, sir.

923
01:45:48,644 --> 01:45:51,204
-回到岗位上  -是
-Back to your station. -Yes, sir.

924
01:45:54,383 --> 01:45:57,580
绑在右手辨别敌我
On your right upper arm, to tell friend from foe.

925
01:45:57,653 --> 01:46:00,281
绑在这只手  你的右手
Davies, this arm. Starboard arm.

926
01:46:00,389 --> 01:46:04,120
-是你断的那只手吗?  -说话小心点
-Is that the arm you got or don't got? -Less of that cheek, Davies.

927
01:46:04,226 --> 01:46:07,992
把领巾绑在右臂
Take your neck cloths and put them round your right upper arm.

928
01:46:08,096 --> 01:46:10,656
船长来了
Make way for the captain.

929
01:46:12,067 --> 01:46:14,126
恭喜了  三副
Congratulations, Lieutenant.

930
01:46:14,236 --> 01:46:15,760
很好  伙伴们
Right, lads.

931
01:46:15,837 --> 01:46:18,169
我知道你们都很英勇
I know there's not a faint heart among you,

932
01:46:18,273 --> 01:46:22,073
你们跟我一样很想杀敌报国
and I know you're as anxious as I am to get into close action.

933
01:46:22,144 --> 01:46:25,739
但是我们要先把他们引过来
But we must bring him right up beside us before we spring this trap.

934
01:46:25,814 --> 01:46:27,805
这要考验我们的胆识
That will test our nerve.

935
01:46:27,916 --> 01:46:31,977
还有纪律  跟勇气一样重要
And discipline will count just as much as courage.

936
01:46:32,087 --> 01:46:37,491
地狱号不好对付  大炮和船员比我们多两倍
The Acheron is a tough nut to crack. More than twice our guns and numbers.

937
01:46:37,593 --> 01:46:40,824
他们会顽强抵抗
And they will sell their lives dearly.

938
01:46:42,664 --> 01:46:46,930
掌帆员  你们要先装得笨手笨脚
Topmen, your handling of the sheets to be lubberly and un-navylike,

939
01:46:47,002 --> 01:46:49,664
等我下令就把帆一收
until the signal to spill the wind from our sails.

940
01:46:49,771 --> 01:46:53,172
我们就会停下来
This will bring us almost to a complete stop.

941
01:46:53,275 --> 01:46:56,870
炮兵要迅速把大炮推出炮门
Gun crews, you must run out and tie down in double-quick time.

942
01:46:56,979 --> 01:46:59,756
没有后轮能射得更高  
With the rear wheels removed you've gained elevation, 

943
01:46:59,757 --> 01:47:02,281
但是却不能重新装弹药
but without recoil you can't reload.

944
01:47:02,351 --> 01:47:07,653
所以左舷大炮只能开一次炮  记着  只能开一次
So, gun captains, that gives you one shot from the larboard battery. One shot only.

945
01:47:07,723 --> 01:47:12,524
瞄准主桅射击  一定要把它击倒
You'll fire for her mainmast. Much will depend on your accuracy.

946
01:47:12,628 --> 01:47:18,967
它就算动不了也很危险  就像受伤的野兽
However, even crippled she will still be dangerous, like a wounded beast.

947
01:47:21,903 --> 01:47:23,962
霍华德队长率领你的陆战队员...
Captain Howard and the marines

948
01:47:24,039 --> 01:47:28,339
要用回旋炮跟毛瑟枪  攻击对方的露天甲板
will sweep their weather deck with swivel gun and musket fire from the tops.

949
01:47:28,410 --> 01:47:31,470
先替我们解决一些敌人
They'll try and even the odds for us before we board.

950
01:47:33,248 --> 01:47:36,809
他们把这艘船当成大肥羊
They mean to take us as a prize.

951
01:47:36,885 --> 01:47:43,586
这艘船如果没有损坏会比较值钱  他们的贪心会害他们送命
And we are worth more to them undamaged. Their greed will be their downfall.

952
01:47:45,427 --> 01:47:48,260
祖国受到入侵者威胁
England is under threat of invasion.

953
01:47:48,363 --> 01:47:52,527
这艘船就是我们的家园
And though we be on the far side of the world, this ship is our home.

954
01:47:54,169 --> 01:47:57,036
这艘船就是祖国
This ship is England.

955
01:48:00,175 --> 01:48:04,703
大家都要坚守岗位  以迅雷不及掩耳之速进攻
So it's every hand to his rope or gun. Quick's the word and sharp's the action.

956
01:48:04,780 --> 01:48:08,216
杀他个措手不及屁滚尿流
After all, surprise is on our side.

957
01:48:19,695 --> 01:48:22,596
丢高一点  让他们看到
-Toss them high so they can see them. -Hello, Doctor.

958
01:48:22,698 --> 01:48:24,063
杰克
Jack.

959
01:48:24,132 --> 01:48:26,396
-抽根雪茄  -不了谢谢
-Care for a cigar? -Thank you, no.

960
01:48:26,468 --> 01:48:29,062
这是你的
If you please, Doctor.

961
01:48:30,472 --> 01:48:33,737
-我替你叫了咖啡  -谢谢
-I took the liberty, Doctor. -Thank you, Killick.

962
01:48:33,809 --> 01:48:38,473
-我加了三块方糖  -你真好心
-There's three lumps in there. -How kind.

963
01:49:33,268 --> 01:49:35,759
-祝好运  威尔  -好运
-Good luck, Will. -Good luck, Peter.

964
01:49:37,539 --> 01:49:41,100
-待会见  -好
-See you afterwards. -And you.

965
01:49:42,144 --> 01:49:45,773
稳住  保持冷静
Steady now, lads. Keep calm.

966
01:49:48,216 --> 01:49:51,811
"妖女号" 捕鲸船  这是地狱号
English whaler Syren, this is Acheron.

967
01:49:53,655 --> 01:49:58,456
你们已经无处可逃  这算是警告
You have no possibility, no chance. But you have had warning.

968
01:49:58,527 --> 01:50:01,985
不停船就把你们炸毁
Stop now, or we will destroy your ship.

969
01:50:02,063 --> 01:50:05,499
英国捕鲸船  这是最后的警告
English whaler, this is your last warning.

970
01:50:05,567 --> 01:50:09,867
不停船就把你们炸毁
Stop now, or we will destroy you.

971
01:50:09,971 --> 01:50:12,201
大家上
Let fly!

972
01:50:14,176 --> 01:50:17,976
拖过去
Haul your yards there.

973
01:50:19,314 --> 01:50:21,475
快点
Run out, boys.

974
01:50:21,550 --> 01:50:22,710
开炮
Fire!

975
01:50:23,919 --> 01:50:25,716
开炮
Fire!

976
01:50:34,596 --> 01:50:37,258
瞄准主桅
For the mainmast, lads.

977
01:50:44,239 --> 01:50:46,707
-让我过去  -开炮
-Let me through. -Fire!

978
01:51:14,302 --> 01:51:16,395
向左急转
Hard a-larboard.

979
01:51:17,105 --> 01:51:19,630
张起前桅帆和中桅帆
Right the headsails. Set the topsails.

980
01:51:19,741 --> 01:51:21,038
升起来
Heave.

981
01:51:22,110 --> 01:51:24,977
快到右舷
Man the starboard battery.

982
01:51:31,119 --> 01:51:33,485
看到目标就开炮
Fire as she bears.

983
01:51:53,975 --> 01:51:56,944
接近
Get to it.

984
01:51:57,012 --> 01:51:59,640
被主桅挡住  过不去
It's the fallen mast. We can't lay alongside.

985
01:51:59,748 --> 01:52:02,774
划小艇试着过去  我会尽量掩护你们
Cross the wreckage as best you can. I'll draw their fire.

986
01:52:02,851 --> 01:52:06,810
-跟普灵一起去  -收起中桅帆
-My division to join Mr Pullings. -Clew up topsails.

987
01:52:06,922 --> 01:52:09,914
幸运杰克万岁
Huzzah for Lucky Jack.

988
01:52:09,991 --> 01:52:12,619
抛出勾绳
Grappling hooks away.

989
01:52:12,694 --> 01:52:15,128
放下登船跳板
Run out the boarding planks.

990
01:52:17,265 --> 01:52:22,430
-跟我来  -为了祖国和这只大肥羊
-My division, follow me. -For England, for home, and for the prize.

991
01:52:23,038 --> 01:52:25,632
冲啊
Here we go, lads.

992
01:52:29,811 --> 01:52:31,870
别出声  安静
Pipe down. Silence.

993
01:52:54,669 --> 01:52:56,660
看来他们全军覆没
Looks like the job is done, sir.

994
01:52:56,738 --> 01:52:58,501
地狱号
Acheron.

995
01:53:12,821 --> 01:53:14,015
开火
Fire!

996
01:53:30,739 --> 01:53:33,105
布雷克尼  快开炮
Mr Blakeney, the nine-pounder.

997
01:53:33,208 --> 01:53:35,073
来吧
That's it.

998
01:53:35,176 --> 01:53:36,234
开炮
Fire!

999
01:53:37,545 --> 01:53:39,843
继续前进  前进
Keep moving, men. Keep moving.

1000
01:54:28,963 --> 01:54:30,828
乔
Joe.

1001
01:54:36,738 --> 01:54:38,330
丢炸弹
Grenades, ready.

1002
01:54:48,516 --> 01:54:51,485
他们瞄准了我们
They're aiming for our hull.

1003
01:54:51,586 --> 01:54:54,248
想把我们炸沉  炮管朝下
They could sink us. Depress the muzzle.

1004
01:54:54,322 --> 01:54:56,347
把后面抬起来
Padeen, train it aft.

1005
01:54:56,458 --> 01:54:58,119
消灭敌人
Together now.

1006
01:54:59,027 --> 01:55:01,188
让开
Stand clear.

1007
01:55:01,262 --> 01:55:03,025
开炮
Fire!

1008
01:55:03,932 --> 01:55:06,332
拿武器攻过去
Arm yourselves. We must board them.

1009
01:55:07,702 --> 01:55:09,795
跟我来
Follow me.

1010
01:55:25,220 --> 01:55:26,983
上啊
Now.

1011
01:55:31,659 --> 01:55:35,789
捕鲸船员  跟我来  快点跟上来
Whalers, follow me. Mr Hogg, down below. Quickly now.

1012
01:55:38,233 --> 01:55:42,033
信天翁号船员  听到吗?
Albatrosses. Albatrosses, do you hear me?

1013
01:55:43,004 --> 01:55:45,029
快阻止他们
To the guns.

1014
01:55:48,643 --> 01:55:50,975
把火药浇熄
Boyle, douse that gun's priming.

1015
01:56:26,181 --> 01:56:29,173
快点  快走
Lively there. Come on. Move.

1016
01:56:32,720 --> 01:56:35,382
英勇杀敌吧
Now do your worst.

1017
01:57:06,754 --> 01:57:08,722
霍华德
-Mr Howard. -Sir.

1018
01:57:08,790 --> 01:57:11,418
-他们降旗了吗?  -降了
-Have they struck their colors? -I believe so.

1019
01:57:11,492 --> 01:57:15,155
-找到船长了吗?  -还没有
-Has their captain been sighted? -Not yet, sir.

1020
01:57:15,263 --> 01:57:17,254
继续吧
-Carry on. -Aye, sir.

1021
01:58:19,127 --> 01:58:21,527
我是狄医生
Docteur de Vigny, monsieur.

1022
01:58:21,629 --> 01:58:24,393
我已经尽力了
I did what I could for him.

1023
01:58:29,504 --> 01:58:33,634
船长死前要我把这把剑交给你
Before the capitaine died, he said I was to give you this.

1024
02:00:03,631 --> 02:00:06,600
不  让我来
No. I'll do it.

1025
02:00:20,314 --> 02:00:22,748
请你帮忙
Can you help me?

1026
02:00:46,607 --> 02:00:48,438
我们在天上的父
Our Father,

1027
02:00:48,509 --> 02:00:52,536
愿人都尊你的名为圣
who art in heaven, hallowed be thy name.

1028
02:00:52,647 --> 02:00:56,515
愿你的国降临  愿你的旨意行在地上
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done,

1029
02:00:56,617 --> 02:00:58,983
如同行在天上
on earth as it is in heaven.

1030
02:00:59,654 --> 02:01:02,384
赐给我们日用的饮食
Give us this day our daily bread,

1031
02:01:02,490 --> 02:01:07,393
免我们的债  如同我们免了人的债
and forgive us our trespasses, as we forgive those who trespass against us.

1032
02:01:07,495 --> 02:01:11,556
不叫我们遇见试探  救我们脱离凶恶
And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

1033
02:01:11,666 --> 02:01:13,634
因为国度
For thine is the kingdom,

1034
02:01:13,701 --> 02:01:15,726
权柄  荣耀
the power and the glory,

1035
02:01:15,837 --> 02:01:17,896
全是你的  直到永远
forever and ever.

1036
02:01:18,005 --> 02:01:19,529
阿门
Amen.

1037
02:01:20,174 --> 02:01:23,632
罗伯特・加德纳  一等水兵
Robert Gardner, able seaman.

1038
02:01:23,711 --> 02:01:27,545
詹姆斯・劳埃德  水手长助手
James Lloyd, boatswain's mate.

1039
02:01:27,648 --> 02:01:30,674
罗伯特・坎普  一等水兵
Robert Kemp, able seaman.

1040
02:01:31,886 --> 02:01:35,822
约翰・安东尼奥  军需官助手
John Antonio, quartermaster's mate.

1041
02:01:37,058 --> 02:01:41,017
迈克尔・杜德  一等水兵
Michael Doudle, able seaman.

1042
02:01:42,530 --> 02:01:46,193
约瑟夫・纳格勒  木工助手
Joseph Nagle, carpenter's mate.

1043
02:01:47,835 --> 02:01:51,066
约翰・艾伦  领航员
John Allen, sailing master.

1044
02:01:56,577 --> 02:01:58,568
彼得・迈尔斯・科勒米
Peter Miles Calamy,

1045
02:02:03,284 --> 02:02:05,548
三副
lieutenant.

1046
02:02:07,955 --> 02:02:11,220
我们将他们的遗体抛入大海
We therefore commit their bodies to the deep,

1047
02:02:11,292 --> 02:02:13,453
让他们腐朽
to be turned into corruption,

1048
02:02:13,561 --> 02:02:17,395
等待大海让他们死而复生
looking for the resurrection of the body when the sea shall give up her dead,

1049
02:02:17,465 --> 02:02:20,366
在天国得到永生
and the life of the world to come,

1050
02:02:20,434 --> 02:02:23,767
以主耶稣基督之名
through our Lord Jesus Christ.

1051
02:02:23,871 --> 02:02:25,930
阿门
Amen.

1052
02:02:54,802 --> 02:02:57,100
我们的老朋友
It's our old friend.

1053
02:03:51,492 --> 02:03:54,484
把油漆传过来
Pass down a barrel of paint, please.

1054
02:04:01,002 --> 02:04:05,166
捕鲸船员和陆战队员都上船了
Sir, the whalers are all aboard and that's the last detachment of marines.

1055
02:04:05,239 --> 02:04:06,866
很好
Good.

1056
02:04:06,974 --> 02:04:09,738
我要回加拉巴哥岛
I think I shall return to the Galapagos.

1057
02:04:09,844 --> 02:04:13,575
补充粮水  让医生找他的鸟
Take on food and water and give the doctor a few days to find his bird.

1058
02:04:13,681 --> 02:04:14,875
好的
Very good, sir.

1059
02:04:14,982 --> 02:04:18,418
你要带地狱号到瓦尔帕莱索港
You, however, shall take the Acheron south to Valparaiso.

1060
02:04:18,519 --> 02:04:23,718
卸下人犯后到朴茨茅斯会合
Parole the prisoners there, refit as necessary, and we shall rendezvous in Portsmouth.

1061
02:04:23,824 --> 02:04:26,850
霍格将会是很好的领航员
I believe Mr Hogg would be a good choice for sailing master.

1062
02:04:26,927 --> 02:04:31,694
我让你自己决定  普灵船长
However, that will be your decision, Captain Pullings.

1063
02:04:36,604 --> 02:04:38,697
这是你的指令
Your orders.

1064
02:04:42,510 --> 02:04:45,240
-谢谢你  -祝你一帆风顺
-Thank you, sir. -Godspeed, Tom.

1065
02:04:45,346 --> 02:04:47,337
你也一样
And to you, sir.

1066
02:04:53,087 --> 02:04:55,055
-莫维?  -我的荣幸
-Mr Mowett? -With pleasure, sir.

1067
02:04:55,122 --> 02:04:57,784
-祝好运  -朴茨茅斯见
-Good luck. -See you in Portsmouth.

1068
02:04:57,892 --> 02:05:01,384
为普灵船长欢呼
Now, lads, huzzah for Captain Pullings.

1069
02:05:09,036 --> 02:05:12,767
-祝你好运  -祝好运  船长
-Good luck, sir. -Good luck, Captain.

1070
02:05:28,789 --> 02:05:30,723
他们又来了
Here we go again.

1071
02:05:30,791 --> 02:05:33,259
基里克  好了吗
Killick. Killick there.

1072
02:05:33,327 --> 02:05:36,125
好了我就会叫你
Which it will be ready when it's ready.

1073
02:05:41,669 --> 02:05:44,604
等他们靠岸我才放心
I'll rest easier when I know they've reached shore.

1074
02:05:44,672 --> 02:05:49,974
这么多伤患  只有可怜的希根照顾
So many wounded, and only that poor unfortunate Higgins to tend to them.

1075
02:05:50,077 --> 02:05:53,740
不过总比没医生来得好
Still, he's better than no doctor at all.

1076
02:05:53,814 --> 02:05:58,615
-我见过地狱号的医生  -他几个月前就发烧死了
-I met their doctor. I spoke to him. -No, he died of fever months ago.

1077
02:05:58,686 --> 02:06:01,280
狄医生吗?
De Vigny?

1078
02:06:12,800 --> 02:06:16,600
-我要见莫维  -莫维请到船长室
-Pass the word for Mr Mowett. -Mr Mowett to the great cabin.

1079
02:06:16,670 --> 02:06:19,696
这是他们的 "医生" 给我的
Their "doctor" gave me this sword.

1080
02:06:21,976 --> 02:06:25,002
改变航向  东南偏东
Mr Mowett, change of course. Southeast by east.

1081
02:06:25,112 --> 02:06:28,604
我们拦截地狱号  并把它护送到瓦尔帕莱索
We'll intercept the Acheron and escort them into Valparaiso.

1082
02:06:28,682 --> 02:06:31,549
遵命  东南偏东
Aye, sir. Sou'east by east.

1083
02:06:32,620 --> 02:06:35,350
威廉
-And William. -Sir?

1084
02:06:35,456 --> 02:06:38,186
-击鼓备战  -好的
-Beat to quarters. -Very good, sir.

1085
02:06:43,230 --> 02:06:46,688
你必须完成任务对吧
Subject to the requirements of the service.

1086
02:06:54,141 --> 02:06:57,474
史蒂芬  那只鸟不会飞吧?
Well, Stephen, the bird's flightless?

1087
02:06:57,545 --> 02:06:58,637
没错
Yes.

1088
02:06:59,713 --> 02:07:02,375
它哪儿也不会去的
It's not going anywhere.

